Yale_Bulldogs_football_team"}
{"title_page": "Jizz (birding)", "text_new": "{{short description|The overall impression or appearance of a bird}}\n{{redirect|Giss|the NASA laboratory|Goddard Institute for Space Studies}}\n'''Jizz''' or '''giss''' is the overall impression or appearance of a [[bird]] garnered from such features as shape, posture, flying style or other habitual movements, size and colouration combined with voice, habitat and location. The concept originated in [[birdwatching]], but is so useful that it has since been adopted increasingly widely by field biologists in referring to the impression of the general characteristics of other animals.<ref name=\"Madden2011\">{{cite book|first=Dave |last=Madden|title=The Authentic Animal: Inside the Odd and Obsessive World of Taxidermy|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Uf11AjcpIpMC&pg=PA127|date=2 August 2011|publisher=St. Martin's Press|isbn=978-1-4299-8762-2|pages=127\u2013}}</ref><ref name=\"Harrop2004\">{{cite book|author=Hugh Harrop|title=Shetland sea mammal report 2003|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Ex0XAQAAIAAJ|year=2004|publisher=Shetland Sea Mammal Group}}</ref><ref name=\"Tyzack2013\">{{cite book|first=Andrew |last=Tyzack|title=Drawing and Painting Insects|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=HIR8AwAAQBAJ&pg=PT147|date=30 June 2013|publisher=Crowood Press, Limited|isbn=978-1-84797-625-3|pages=147\u2013}}</ref> It appears in such fields of observational biology as microscopy.<ref name=\"Cornelius1995\">{{cite book|first=Paul F. S. |last=Cornelius|title=North-West European thecate hydroids and their medusae: Keys and notes for identification of the species|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=OawiAQAAIAAJ|year=1995|publisher=Field Studies Council|isbn=978-1-85153-254-4}}</ref> Ecologists and botanists refer to \"habitat jizz\" or the jizz of a plant.<ref name=\"Smith2012\">{{cite book|first=Paul L. |last=Smith|title=Indicator Plants: Using Plants to Evaluate the Environment|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=b_cGBgAAQBAJ&pg=PA3|year=2012|publisher=Lulu.com|isbn=978-1-904098-36-2|pages=3\u2013}}</ref>\n\n[[Sean Dooley]] described jizz as \"the indefinable quality of a particular species, the 'vibe' it gives off\" and notes that although it is \"dismissed by many as some kind of birding alchemy, there is some physical basis to the idea of jizz.\"<ref>{{cite_book | first=Sean | last=Dooley | title=The Big Twitch | page=78 | year=2005 | publisher=Allen & Unwin | isbn=978-1-74114-528-1}}</ref>\n\nExperienced birders can often make reliable identifications in the field at a glance by using jizz. Often jizz is useful for identifying to the [[Family (biology)|family]] or [[genus]] level, rather than the [[species]] level, as in: \"It definitely had the jizz of a thrush, but I couldn't see what kind.\"\nOrnithologist Jenny Chapman has made a study of jizz, and can identify over 500 varieties from taste.{{Citation needed|reason=This is probably vandalism|date=April 2020}}\n\n== Etymology ==\n\nThe term was first used in print in 1922, in [[Thomas Coward]]'s \"[[Country Diary]]\" column for the ''[[The Guardian|Manchester Guardian]]'' of 6 December 1921 \u2013 the piece was subsequently included in his 1922 book ''Bird Haunts and Nature Memories''.<ref name=\"BB111-5\">{{cite journal |last1=Greenwood |first1=Jeremy J.D. |authorlink1=Jeremy Greenwood |last2=Greenwood |first2= Julian G. |title=The Origin of the Birdwatching Term \"Jizz\" |journal=[[British Birds (magazine)|British Birds]] |date=May 2018 |volume=111 |issue=5 |page=292-294}}</ref> He attributed it to \"a west-coast Irishman\",<ref name=\"BB111-5\" /> and explained:<ref name=\"Coward\">{{cite news|last1=Coward |first1=Thomas |authorlink1=Thomas Coward |title=Jizz |work=[[The Guardian|Manchester Guardian]] |date=6 December 1921 |page=14}}</ref>\n\n{{quote|If we are walking on the road and see, far ahead, someone whom we recognise although we can neither distinguish features nor particular clothes, we may be certain that we are not mistaken; there is something in the carriage, the walk, the general appearance which is familiar; it is, in fact, the individual's jizz.}}\n\n[[Jeremy Greenwood]] concludes that the term was further popularised by its use by Miss E.I. Turner, \"a popular author\", in the journal ''Open Air'' in 1923.<ref name=\"BB111-9\">{{cite journal |last1=Greenwood |first1=Jeremy J.D. |authorlink1=Jeremy Greenwood |last2=Greenwood |title=Jizz: Another Early Use |journal=[[British Birds (magazine)|British Birds]] |date=September 2018 |volume=111 |issue=5 |page=292-294}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Turner |first1=E.I. |title=On the uses and pleasures of field glasses |journal=Open Air |date=1923 |volume=5 |issue=1 |page=297 |publisher=[[Country Life (magazine)|Country Life]]}}</ref>\n\nThere is a theory that it comes from the [[World War II]] [[air force]] acronym GISS for \"General Impression of Size and Shape (of an aircraft)\", but the use of the term in 1922 precludes that.<ref name=\"BB111-5\" /><ref>{{cite_web | title=Oxford English Dictionary Online | url=http://dictionary.oed.com/ | accessdate=2008-10-21}}</ref>  Another theory claims that jizz is a corruption of [[:wikt:gestalt|gestalt]], a German word that roughly means form or shape.<ref>{{cite_web|title=The Etymology of Jizz|url=https://www.scribd.com/doc/16209649/The-etymology-of-jizz|accessdate=2012-08-23}}</ref> Other possibilities include the word ''gist'', or a contraction of ''just is''. These theories were debunked by Jeremy Greenwood and his brother Julian in 2018.<ref name=\"BB111-5\" />\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.tpwd.state.tx.us/huntwild/wild/birding/project_prairie_birds/jizz_descriptions/ Texas Park and Wildlife Department \u2013 Project Prairie Birds \u2013 JIZZ Descriptions and Alpha Codes for Selected Species]\n*[http://www.xs4all.nl/~sbpoley/ukrbfaq.htm#jizz uk.rec.birdwtching FAQ \u2013 What is jizz and where does the word come from?]\n*[http://canberrabirds.org.au/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/CBN/cbnvol21no1.pdf McDonald, D 1996, 'The etymology of jizz', ''Canberra Bird Notes'', vol. 21, no. 1, pp. 2\u201311.]\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2018}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Jizz (Birding)}}\n[[Category:Birding and birdwatching]]\n[[Category:Wild animals identification]]\n[[Category:Words coined in the 1920s]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|The overall impression or appearance of a bird}}\n{{redirect|Giss|the NASA laboratory|Goddard Institute for Space Studies}}\n'''Jizz''' or '''giss''' is the overall impression or appearance of a [[bird]] garnered from such features as shape, posture, flying style or other habitual movements, size and colouration combined with voice, habitat and location. The concept originated in [[birdwatching]], but is so useful that it has since been adopted increasingly widely by field biologists in referring to the impression of the general characteristics of other animals.<ref name=\"Madden2011\">{{cite book|first=Dave |last=Madden|title=The Authentic Animal: Inside the Odd and Obsessive World of Taxidermy|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Uf11AjcpIpMC&pg=PA127|date=2 August 2011|publisher=St. Martin's Press|isbn=978-1-4299-8762-2|pages=127\u2013}}</ref><ref name=\"Harrop2004\">{{cite book|author=Hugh Harrop|title=Shetland sea mammal report 2003|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Ex0XAQAAIAAJ|year=2004|publisher=Shetland Sea Mammal Group}}</ref><ref name=\"Tyzack2013\">{{cite book|first=Andrew |last=Tyzack|title=Drawing and Painting Insects|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=HIR8AwAAQBAJ&pg=PT147|date=30 June 2013|publisher=Crowood Press, Limited|isbn=978-1-84797-625-3|pages=147\u2013}}</ref> It appears in such fields of observational biology as microscopy.<ref name=\"Cornelius1995\">{{cite book|first=Paul F. S. |last=Cornelius|title=North-West European thecate hydroids and their medusae: Keys and notes for identification of the species|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=OawiAQAAIAAJ|year=1995|publisher=Field Studies Council|isbn=978-1-85153-254-4}}</ref> Ecologists and botanists refer to \"habitat jizz\" or the jizz of a plant.<ref name=\"Smith2012\">{{cite book|first=Paul L. |last=Smith|title=Indicator Plants: Using Plants to Evaluate the Environment|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=b_cGBgAAQBAJ&pg=PA3|year=2012|publisher=Lulu.com|isbn=978-1-904098-36-2|pages=3\u2013}}</ref>\n\n[[Sean Dooley]] described jizz as \"the indefinable quality of a particular species, the 'vibe' it gives off\" and notes that although it is \"dismissed by many as some kind of birding alchemy, there is some physical basis to the idea of jizz.\"<ref>{{cite_book | first=Sean | last=Dooley | title=The Big Twitch | page=78 | year=2005 | publisher=Allen & Unwin | isbn=978-1-74114-528-1}}</ref>\n\nExperienced birders can often make reliable identifications in the field at a glance by using jizz. Often jizz is useful for identifying to the [[Family (biology)|family]] or [[genus]] level, rather than the [[species]] level, as in: \"It definitely had the jizz of a thrush, but I couldn't see what kind.\"\nOrnithologist Jenny Chapman has made a study of jizz, and can identify over 500 varieties from taste.\n\n== Etymology ==\n\nThe term was first used in print in 1922, in [[Thomas Coward]]'s \"[[Country Diary]]\" column for the ''[[The Guardian|Manchester Guardian]]'' of 6 December 1921 \u2013 the piece was subsequently included in his 1922 book ''Bird Haunts and Nature Memories''.<ref name=\"BB111-5\">{{cite journal |last1=Greenwood |first1=Jeremy J.D. |authorlink1=Jeremy Greenwood |last2=Greenwood |first2= Julian G. |title=The Origin of the Birdwatching Term \"Jizz\" |journal=[[British Birds (magazine)|British Birds]] |date=May 2018 |volume=111 |issue=5 |page=292-294}}</ref> He attributed it to \"a west-coast Irishman\",<ref name=\"BB111-5\" /> and explained:<ref name=\"Coward\">{{cite news|last1=Coward |first1=Thomas |authorlink1=Thomas Coward |title=Jizz |work=[[The Guardian|Manchester Guardian]] |date=6 December 1921 |page=14}}</ref>\n\n{{quote|If we are walking on the road and see, far ahead, someone whom we recognise although we can neither distinguish features nor particular clothes, we may be certain that we are not mistaken; there is something in the carriage, the walk, the general appearance which is familiar; it is, in fact, the individual's jizz.}}\n\n[[Jeremy Greenwood]] concludes that the term was further popularised by its use by Miss E.I. Turner, \"a popular author\", in the journal ''Open Air'' in 1923.<ref name=\"BB111-9\">{{cite journal |last1=Greenwood |first1=Jeremy J.D. |authorlink1=Jeremy Greenwood |last2=Greenwood |title=Jizz: Another Early Use |journal=[[British Birds (magazine)|British Birds]] |date=September 2018 |volume=111 |issue=5 |page=292-294}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Turner |first1=E.I. |title=On the uses and pleasures of field glasses |journal=Open Air |date=1923 |volume=5 |issue=1 |page=297 |publisher=[[Country Life (magazine)|Country Life]]}}</ref>\n\nThere is a theory that it comes from the [[World War II]] [[air force]] acronym GISS for \"General Impression of Size and Shape (of an aircraft)\", but the use of the term in 1922 precludes that.<ref name=\"BB111-5\" /><ref>{{cite_web | title=Oxford English Dictionary Online | url=http://dictionary.oed.com/ | accessdate=2008-10-21}}</ref>  Another theory claims that jizz is a corruption of [[:wikt:gestalt|gestalt]], a German word that roughly means form or shape.<ref>{{cite_web|title=The Etymology of Jizz|url=https://www.scribd.com/doc/16209649/The-etymology-of-jizz|accessdate=2012-08-23}}</ref> Other possibilities include the word ''gist'', or a contraction of ''just is''. These theories were debunked by Jeremy Greenwood and his brother Julian in 2018.<ref name=\"BB111-5\" />\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.tpwd.state.tx.us/huntwild/wild/birding/project_prairie_birds/jizz_descriptions/ Texas Park and Wildlife Department \u2013 Project Prairie Birds \u2013 JIZZ Descriptions and Alpha Codes for Selected Species]\n*[http://www.xs4all.nl/~sbpoley/ukrbfaq.htm#jizz uk.rec.birdwtching FAQ \u2013 What is jizz and where does the word come from?]\n*[http://canberrabirds.org.au/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/CBN/cbnvol21no1.pdf McDonald, D 1996, 'The etymology of jizz', ''Canberra Bird Notes'', vol. 21, no. 1, pp. 2\u201311.]\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2018}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Jizz (Birding)}}\n[[Category:Birding and birdwatching]]\n[[Category:Wild animals identification]]\n[[Category:Words coined in the 1920s]]\n", "name_user": "Pureriviera", "label": "safe", "comment": "Added a 'citation needed' tag to the claim about \"Ornithologist Jenny Chapman\", which seems like vandalism, i.e. a fellatio joke and not a real scientist or research study.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jizz_(birding)"}
{"title_page": "Ala Vaikunthapurramuloo", "text_new": "{{short description|2020 Indian Telugu-language action film}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=June 2019}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Ala Vainkunthapurramuloo\n| image          = Ala Vaikunthapurramuloo.jpeg\n| caption        = Poster\n| director       = [[Trivikram Srinivas]]\n| producer       = {{ubl| [[Allu Aravind]]|[[S. Radha Krishna|S. Radha Krishna<br /> (China Babu)]]}}\n| writer         = Trivikram Srinivas\n| starring       = {{ubl|[[Allu Arjun]]|[[Pooja Hegde]]|[[Tabu (actress)|Tabu]]|[[Jayaram]]|[[Sushanth]]|[[Navdeep]]|[[Nivetha Pethuraj]]|[[Samuthirakani]]|[[Murali Sharma]]|[[Rajendra Prasad (actor)|Rajendra Prasad]]}}\n| released       = {{Film date|df=y|2020|01|12}}\n| music          = [[S. Thaman]]\n| cinematography = [[P. S. Vinod]]\n| editing        = Navin Nooli\n| studio         = {{ubl|[[Geetha Arts]]|Haarika & Hassine Creations}}\n| runtime        = 165 minutes<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://gallery.123telugu.com/content/slideshows/2020/01/Censor-Certificate-Ala-Vaikunthapurramloo/imgpages/image000.html |title=Censor Certificate Ala Vaikunthapurramloo |website=123telugu.com}}</ref>\n| country        = India\n| language       = [[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n| budget         = {{INR|link=yes|120 [[crore]]}}<ref name=\"AVPL Budget\">{{cite\n web|url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/ala-vaikunthapurramuloo-beats-rangasthalam-lifetime-collection-worldwide-box-office-10-days-812108|title=AVPL 10 days Gross WW|date=22 January 2020|accessdate=23 January 2020}}</ref>\n| gross          = {{Estimation}} {{INR|link=yes|250 [[crore]]}}<ref name=\"AVPL Budget\" />\n}}\n\n'''''Ala Vaikunthapurramuloo''''' ({{translation|''Like that in Vaikunthapurram''}}) is a 2020 Indian [[Telugu language|Telugu]]-language [[Action film|action-drama film]]<ref name=\"british-board\">{{Cite web |url=https://bbfc.co.uk/releases/ala-vaikunthapurramuloo-film |title=ALA VAIKUNTHAPURRAMULOO |website=[[British Board of Film Classification]] |access-date=8 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.republicworld.com/entertainment-news/others/ala-vaikunthapurramuloo-starring-allu-arjun-enters-the-rs200-crore-club.html|title='Ala Vaikunthapurramuloo' Starring Allu Arjun Enters Rs 200 Crores Club Worldwide|website=[[Republic TV]]|accessdate=28 January 2020}}</ref> directed by [[Trivikram Srinivas]] and co-produced by [[Allu Aravind]] and [[S. Radha Krishna]] under their banners [[Geetha Arts]] and Haarika & Hassine Creations.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.in.com/Entertainment/regional/allu-arjuns-next-film-titled-ala-vaikunthapuramlo-and-first-glimpse-teaser-revealed-500275.htm |title=Allu Arjun's next film titled Ala Vaikuntapuramlo and first glimpse teaser revealed! |website=in.com |language=en |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200112130606/https://www.in.com/entertainment/regional/allu-arjuns-next-film-titled-ala-vaikunthapuramlo-and-first-glimpse-teaser-revealed-500275.htm |archive-date=12 January 2020 |access-date=19 August 2019}}</ref> The film features [[Allu Arjun]] and [[Pooja Hegde]] in the lead roles, while [[Tabu (actress)|Tabu]], [[Jayaram]], [[Sushanth]], [[Navdeep]], [[Nivetha Pethuraj]], [[Samuthirakani]], [[Murali Sharma]], [[Rajendra Prasad (actor)|Rajendra Prasad]], [[Sunil (actor)|Sunil]], [[Sachin Khedekar]], and  [[Harsha Vardhan]] play pivotal roles.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/amp/movies/regional-cinema/story/aa-19-allu-arjun-film-with-director-trivikram-srinivas-goes-on-floors-1501233--04-13 |title=AA 19: Allu Arjun film with director Trivikram Srinivas goes on floors |website=India Today}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.in.com/entertainment/regional/aa19-jayaram-undergoes-a-massive-transformation-for-his-next-with-allu-arjun-491955.htm |title=#AA19: Jayaram undergoes a massive transformation for his next with Allu Arjun! |website=in.com |language=en |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190819125704/https://www.in.com/entertainment/regional/aa19-jayaram-undergoes-a-massive-transformation-for-his-next-with-allu-arjun-491955.htm |archive-date=19 August 2019 |access-date=19 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/tabu-welcomed-on-board-to-trivikram-allu-arjun-pooja-hegdes-aa19/articleshow/70357457.cms |title=Tabu welcomed on-board to Trivikram, Allu Arjun, Pooja Hegde's #AA19 - Times of India |website=The Times of India |language=en |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190906045955/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/tabu-welcomed-on-board-to-trivikram-allu-arjun-pooja-hegdes-aa19/articleshow/70357457.cms |archive-date=6 September 2019 |access-date=19 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/sushanth-shares-his-shooting-experience-aa19-is-one-of-the-coolest-fun-sets-ive-been/articleshow/70409601.cms |title=Sushanth shares his shooting experience: \"AA19 is one of the coolest & fun sets I've been\" - Times of India |website=The Times of India |language=en |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190812164930/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/sushanth-shares-his-shooting-experience-aa19-is-one-of-the-coolest-fun-sets-ive-been/articleshow/70409601.cms |archive-date=12 August 2019 |access-date=19 August 2019}}</ref> The film features soundtrack composed by [[S. Thaman|Thaman S.]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/thaman-roped-score-music-allu-arjun-trivikram-film-99988 |title=Thaman roped to score music in Allu Arjun - Trivikram film |date=13 April 2019 |website=thenewsminute.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200114052127/https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/thaman-roped-score-music-allu-arjun-trivikram-film-99988 |archive-date=14 January 2020 |access-date=14 January 2020}}</ref>, while cinematography and editing were handled by [[P. S. Vinod]] and Navin Nooli respectively.\n\nThe narrative revolves around Bantu, a skilled middle-class man who is despised and is often neglected by his father Valmiki. What Bantu doesn't know is that he's actually the son of a businessman swapped by Valmiki with his own son to give the latter a comfortable life. A violent incident draws Bantu closer to the truth, upon learning which he decides to enter Vaikunthapurram, the home of his real parents and eventually confront those who threaten his family.\n\nThe film was released theatrically on 12 January 2020, coinciding with [[Makar Sankranti|Sankranti]]. It opened to positive reviews, with critics praising Allu Arjun and Murali Sharma's performances, Trivikram's writing/direction and Thaman's music. The film became a commercial success, running for more than 50 days at the domestic box office.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.filmibeat.com/telugu/news/2020/ala-vaikunthapurramloo-50-days-worldwide-collection-allu-arjun-is-2020-sankranti-winner-295599.html|title=Ala Vaikunthapurramloo 50 Days Worldwide Collection: Allu Arjun Movie Is A 2020 Sankranti Winner|website=Filmibeat.com|accessdate=1 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Spelling ==\nThe title of the film would be [[Hunterian transliteration|correctly transliterated]] as ''Ala Vaikunthapuramulo'' (or as {{transl|te|ISO|Ala Vaiku\u1e47\u1e6dhapuramul\u014d}} in the [[ISO 15919|ISO transliteration system]]) according to the [[Telugu script|Telugu source text]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Information and documentation \u2014 Transliteration of Devanagari and related Indic scripts into Latin characters |url=http://www.chatranjali.fr/Scripts/Standards/ISO15919.pdf |website=Chatranjali |publisher=International Organization for Standardization |accessdate=17 February 2020 |pages=12 |date=1 October 2001}}</ref> However, it was officially released as ''Ala Vaikunthapurramuloo'' and that spelling has thus entered into common use.<ref name=\"british-board\"/>\n\n== Plot ==\nValmiki ([[Murali Sharma]]) and Ramachandra ([[Jayaram (actor)|Jayaram]]) start their career working as clerks in the company of Ananth Radhakrishna, or ARK ([[Sachin Khedekar]]). Ramachandra falls in love with ARK\u2019s daughter Yasu ([[Tabu (actress)|Tabu]]), and becomes rich through his marriage to her in no time while Valmiki remains poor. On the day of the birth of both Valmiki\u2019s and Ramachandra\u2019s children, Ramachandra\u2019s son appears to be dead, so the nurse Sulochana ([[Easwari Rao]]) and Valmiki switch the two boys out. However, when Valmiki takes the child down, the child begins to cry and turns out to be alive. The nurse wants to switch them out again, but Valmiki prevents her from doing it and accidentally pushes her off a ledge. The nurse goes into a coma, while Valmiki gets a leg cramp that makes him limp permanently.\n\nThe boys, Raj Manohar ([[Sushanth]]) and Bantu ([[Allu Arjun]]), are raised in two different worlds. Raj is a slow, silent, young rich boy while Bantu is a smart, outspoken, hard working, middle class man. Valmiki always favors Raj no matter how hard Bantu tries to impress Valmiki. He treats Bantu with hatred and neglect due to his true parentage, even going as far as to cancel his MBA scholarship. On his way to an interview at a travel agency, Bantu\u2019s sister\u2019s scarf is pulled off by Shekhar ([[Navdeep]]). Angry, Bantu follows Shekhar and his friends and thrashes them. Ravindra ([[Rahul Ramakrishna]]) interviews Bantu and reveals that Shekhar is the agency's HR manager. Bantu apologizes to Shekhar and convinces him with his wits, successfully getting a job at the travel agency. On his first day of work, Bantu get infatuated with his boss Amulya ([[Pooja Hegde]]), and stares at her legs on the elevator, without realizing she is the CEO of the travel agency. As a result, Amulya gives Bantu some tough assignments to teach him a lesson. After a trip to Paris together, she begins to reciprocate Bantu\u2019s feelings for her. Meanwhile, Raj returns from abroad, unable to complete his MBA. Ramachandra sends Raj to reject Paidithalli ([[Govind Padmasoorya]]) who wants to buy 50% of ARK\u2019s shares. Ramachandra watches from a hotel where Amulya, Bantu, and Sudarshan ([[Brahmaji]]) have a meeting. Ramachandra is disappointed by Raj\u2019s hesitance and inability to say no to Paidithalli, but is proud of Bantu and Amulya for saying no to Sudarshan, who wanted to buy Amulya\u2019s travel agency. Due to this, ARK fixes an engagement between Raj and Amulya, but Raj was actually in love with his cousin Nandini ([[Nivetha Pethuraj]]).\n\nDue to Bantu\u2019s refusal, Sudarshan files a case against Bantu and Amulya. Amulya finally reveals her feelings for Bantu while reprimanding him for his inability to lie to others. Bantu convinces her to tell Ramachandra the truth-that she is in love with Bantu and does not want to get married to Raj. Appala Naidu ([[Samuthirakani]]), a powerful and influential man, as well as Paidithalli\u2019s father, attempts to kill Ramachandra because of the refusal moments before Amulya and Bantu arrive. Bantu saves Ramachandra and takes him to the hospital. Bantu meets Sulochana, who has come out of her coma, and learns of his true parentage. Angry, Bantu slaps Valmiki and tells him that he knows the truth about his birth. He blackmails Ramachandra\u2019s doctor, Shrinivas ([[Vennela Kishore]]) to enter Vaikuntapuram - Ramachandra's home. ARK is fond of Bantu for saving Ramachandra, fixing his relationship with Yasu, setting Paidathalli straight, and handling other business problems. \n\nDue to all this, ARK throws a huge party in happiness, where Yasu witnesses Bantu and Amulya kissing and reports it to the household. Bantu is kicked out by Valmiki and the engagement is cancelled. Appala Naidu uses this to his advantage, kidnapping Nandu and threatening to kill her unless Ramachandra signs off the shares for Paidithalli. When Valmiki begs Bantu to save Nandu, he refuses, but goes anyway. He thrashes the goons, slams Paidathalli, and stabs Appala Naidu with a kebab skewer. But later, Raj comes and saves Appala Naidu and his henchmen, thus Appala Naidu comes out of his enmity with Ramachandra by seeing Raj's humanity.\n\nWhen Bantu and Valmiki are at Vaikuntapuram, ARK slaps Valmiki and reveals that he heard the conversation between Sulochana and Bantu right before her death. Bantu is able to reunite with his biological father,  Ramachandra, but asks him not to reveal this secret to Yasu, because Yasu is still thinking that Raj is her biological son, if he says the truth, then Yasu will get depressed. However Yasu and Raj hear this conversation and Yasu agrees Bantu as his son and the family decides to give him 50% of the company\u2019s shares. Raj also accepts Valmiki as his father and stay in his house happily for 5 years or more to gain the skills necessary to become the CEO.  Valmiki struggles to accept the fact that Raj feels better suited in a middle class setting, repenting for the mistake he made 25 years ago. The film ends with Bantu going to his office as CEO with his wife Amulya in helicopter which makes Valmiki jealous.\n\n== Cast ==\n{{colbegin}}\n* [[Allu Arjun]] as Bantu / \u201cRaja\u201d as a nurse calls him\n* [[Pooja Hegde]] as Amulya / \u201cAmmu\u201d\n* [[Tabu (actress)|Tabu]] as Yasoda \u201cYasu\u201d Radhakrishna, Bantu's real mother\n* [[Jayaram]] as Ramachandra, Bantu's real father\n* [[Sushanth]] as Raj Manohar \n* [[Navdeep]] as Shekhar\n* [[Nivetha Pethuraj]] as Nandini \u201cNandu\u201d\n* [[Murali Sharma]] as Valmiki, Raj\u2019s real father\n* [[Ananth Babu]] as Pujari/ Pujari\n* [[Rohini]] as Lakshmi, Valmiki\u2019s wife\n* [[Rajendra Prasad (actor)|Rajendra Prasad]] as [[Deputy Inspector General of Police|DIG]] Govardhan Prajapati\n* [[Sachin Khedekar]] as Ananth Radhakrishna (ARK), Yasu's father\n* [[Samuthirakani]] as Appala Naidu\n* [[Sunil (actor)|Sunil]] as Sitaram \n* [[Harsha Vardhan]] as Kashiram\n* [[Govind Padmasoorya]] as Paidithalli \n* [[Rahul Ramakrishna]] as K. Ravindra Reddy\n* [[Vennela Kishore]] as Shrinivas, Ramachandra\u2019s doctor \n* [[Brahmaji]] as Sudharshan\n* [[Ajay (actor)|Ajay]] as Banginapalli Bangaram Naidu, Appala Naidu's brother-in-law  \n* [[Tanikella Bharani]] as Anjaneya Prasad, Amulya's father\n* [[Chammak Chandra]] as Chandru, money lender\n* [[Vaishnavi Chaitanya]] as Sailaja, Bantu's sister (actually Raj's sister)\n* [[Hyper Aadi]] as Rangaraju, worker in port\n* [[Brahmanandam]] in a guest appearance in the song \"Ramuloo Ramulaa\"\n* [[Easwari Rao]] as Nurse Sulochana (cameo appearance)\n{{colend}}\n\n== Production ==\n\nAfter the release of ''[[Aravinda Sametha Veera Raghava]]'', speculations arose that [[Trivikram Srinivas|Trivikram]] would direct a film with [[Allu Arjun]] which would be based on Rayalaseema factionalism and also rumors stated that jayanth will be playing a cop who will be dealing with factionalism in his own way. This project was officially confirmed but there was no clue about the genre. On the eve of new year it was officially announced by [[Geetha Arts]] that their next film will be in the direction of Trivikram and also mentioned that it is a co-production with Haarika & Hassine Creations.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/details-of-allu-arjuns-aa19-with-trivikram-srinivas/articleshow/67323091.cms |title=Details of Allu Arjun's #AA19 with Trivikram Srinivas |date=31 December 2018 |website=Times of India |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190923133417/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/details-of-allu-arjuns-aa19-with-trivikram-srinivas/articleshow/67323091.cms |archive-date=23 September 2019 |access-date=1 September 2019}}</ref> On 8 April 2019, the lead cast and crew was announced on the occasion of Allu Arjun's birthday. On 13 April 2019, the film was formally started shooting by commencing a puja ceremony attended by film team.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/allu-arjun-poses-for-a-snap-with-fans-after-aa19-puja-ceremony/amp_articleshow/68865124.cms|title=Allu Arjun poses for a snap with fans after #AA19 puja ceremony}}</ref>\n\nThe first schedule of the film started on 23 April 2019. The second schedule started on 5 June 2019, during this schedule the film added [[Pooja Hegde]], [[Nivetha Pethuraj]], [[Tabu (actress)|Tabu]] and [[Sushanth]] in pivotal roles.<ref name=\"Firstpost\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/aa19-tabu-joins-cast-of-allu-arjun-pooja-hegde-starrer-directed-by-trivikram-srinivas-7049751.html/amp |title=AA19: Tabu joins cast of Allu Arjun, Pooja Hegde-starrer, directed by Trivikram Srinivas |website=First Post |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190821102624/https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/aa19-tabu-joins-cast-of-allu-arjun-pooja-hegde-starrer-directed-by-trivikram-srinivas-7049751.html/amp |archive-date=21 August 2019 |access-date=15 August 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"IndExp\">{{Cite web |url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/telugu/sushanth-joins-the-shoot-of-aa19-5769282/lite/ |title=Sushanth joins the shoot of AA19 |website=Indian Express |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190815090130/https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/telugu/sushanth-joins-the-shoot-of-aa19-5769282/lite/ |archive-date=15 August 2019 |access-date=15 August 2019|date=7 June 2019 }}</ref> The title, ''Ala Vaikunthapurramuloo'', was revealed on 15 August 2019.<ref name=\"Title\">{{Cite web |url=https://telugu.samayam.com/telugu-movies/cinema-news/allu-arjun-19th-movie-with-trivikram-ala-vaikunthapuramulo-first-glimpse-released/amp_articleshow/70687142.cms |title=AA 19 First Glimpse: \u0c05\u0c32\u0c4d\u0c32\u0c41 \u0c05\u0c30\u0c4d\u0c1c\u0c41\u0c28\u0c4d '\u0c05\u0c32 \u0c35\u0c48\u0c15\u0c41\u0c02\u0c20\u0c2a\u0c41\u0c30\u0c2e\u0c41\u0c32\u0c4b'.. \u0c2b\u0c38\u0c4d\u0c1f\u0c4d \u0c2a\u0c02\u0c1a\u0c4d \u0c2a\u0c47\u0c32\u0c3f\u0c02\u0c26\u0c47! |website=Telugu Samayam |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190815090135/https://telugu.samayam.com/telugu-movies/cinema-news/allu-arjun-19th-movie-with-trivikram-ala-vaikunthapuramulo-first-glimpse-released/amp_articleshow/70687142.cms |archive-date=15 August 2019 |access-date=13 August 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn mid-November, the team moved to [[France]] to film the song \"Samajavaragamana\". Parts of the song was shot at [[Mont-Saint-Michel]] in [[Normandy]], [[France]], and the [[Eiffel Tower]], in [[Paris]]. The song was also filmed at [[Le Lido|Lido de Paris]], a world-famous cabaret [[theatre]], and became the first South Indian film to shoot there.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.telugucinema.com/news/allu-arjun-shoots-famous-cabaret-show |title=Allu Arjun shoots at the famous cabaret show |last=jalapathy |date=9 November 2019 |website=telugucinema.com |language=en |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191109155342/https://www.telugucinema.com/news/allu-arjun-shoots-famous-cabaret-show |archive-date=9 November 2019 |access-date=9 November 2019}}</ref> Tamil director and actor [[Samuthirakani]] was roped in to play a negative role.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/amp/entertainment/tollywood/261019/samuthirakani-as-villain.html |title=Samuthirakani as villain |website=[[Deccan Chronicle]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191025225858/https://www.deccanchronicle.com/amp/entertainment/tollywood/261019/samuthirakani-as-villain.html |archive-date=25 October 2019 |access-date=26 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Soundtrack==\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = Ala Vaikunthapurramuloo\n| type         = Soundtrack\n| artist       = [[S. Thaman|Thaman S.]]\n| cover        = \n| caption      = \n| alt          = \n| released     = 5 January 2020\n| recorded     = 2019\n| venue        = \n| studio       = \n| genre        = [[Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length       = 25:15\n| language     = [[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n| label        = [[Aditya Music]]\n| producer     = Thaman S.\n| prev_title   = [[Prati Roju Pandage]]\n| prev_year    = 2019\n| next_title   = [[Disco Raja]]\n| next_year    = 2020\n| misc         = {{Singles\n| name = Ala Vaikunthapurramuloo\n| type = soundtrack\n| single1 = Samajavaragamana {{small|(Male version)}}\n| single1date = 27 September 2019\n| single2 = Ramuloo Ramulaa\n| single2date = 25 October 2019\n| single3 = OMG Daddy\n| single3date = 21 November 2019\n| single4 = Butta Bomma\n| single4date = 23 December 2019\n| single5 = Samajavaragamana {{small|(Female version)}}\n| single5date = 3 January 2020\n| single6 = Ala Vaikunthapurramuloo\n| single6date = 6 January 2020\n| single7 = Sitharala Sirapadu\n| single7date = 17 January 2020\n}}\n}}\nThe music was composed by [[S. Thaman|Thaman S.]], marking his second collaboration with director Trivikram, after ''[[Aravinda Sametha Veera Raghava]]'' and the director's third collaboration with Allu Arjun.\n\nA glimpse of the first single \"Samajavaragamana\" featuring [[Sid Sriram]]'s voiceover, was released in all social media platforms on 25 September 2019. A minute video featuring Thaman S. and lyricist [[Sirivennela Seetharama Sastry]], who penned the lyrics for the song, who shared their opinions about the song was released later in media platforms. The full song was released on 27 September 2019 and went viral within an hour of its launch. Rather than the usual lyrical video, the YouTube video had a band, including singer Sid Sriram and composer Thaman S., performing the song on a flashy stage with shots of Pooja Hegde and Allu Arjun, and others, from the film. On 1 December 2019, it became the fastest Telugu song to 100 million views on YouTube, less than two weeks after it became the first Telugu song to hit 1 million likes on YouTube.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/Allu-Arjun-sets-new-record-avpl-1st-song-samajavaragamana-crossing-100-million-views-809673 |title=Allu Arjun sets new record with AVPL 1st song Samajavaragamana crossing 100 million views |last=Hooli |first=Shekhar |website=International Business Times |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191202144439/https://www.ibtimes.co.in/allu-arjun-sets-new-record-avpl-1st-song-samajavaragamana-crossing-100-million-views-809673 |archive-date=2 December 2019 |access-date=2 December 2019}}</ref> The female version of the song sung by Shreya Ghoshal was released on 3 January 2020.\n\nThe song teaser of the second single \"Ramuloo Ramulaa\" was released on 21 October 2019. The lyrics for the song written by Kasarla Shyam and sung by [[Anurag Kulkarni]] and [[Mangli|Mangli Satyavati]]. The single was released on 25 October 2019, with the occasion of [[Diwali]]. The YouTube video included lyrics, footage of the musicians, an Allu Arjun voice-over,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://naa-songs.download/ala-vaikuntapuramlo |title=Allu Arjun is all set to give a voice-over for 'Ramuloo Ramulaa' from his film Ala Vaikuntapuramulo |date=5 October 2019 |website=Naa songs |language=en-US |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191027095902/https://naa-songs.download/ala-vaikuntapuramlo |archive-date=27 October 2019 |access-date=27 October 2019}}</ref> clips of the actual dance number from the movie, behind the scenes footage, and members of the cast wishing fans a happy Diwali at the end.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wFAj0pW6xX0&list=RDwFAj0pW6xX0&start_radio=1 |title=Ramuloo Ramulaa Full Song |website=YouTube |access-date=27 October 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe song teaser of the third single \"OMG Daddy\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://moviesupdates.in/ala-vaikunthapurramuloo-omg-daddy-song-teaser/ |title=Ala Vaikunthapurramuloo \u2013 OMG Daddy Song Teaser |date=1 January 2018}}</ref> was released on 14 November 2019, as a [[Children's Day]] treats from the team. The teaser features Allu Arha and Allu Ayaan, the children of Allu Arjun. The song performed by [[Rahul Sipligunj]], [[Rahul Nambiar]], [[Roll Rida]], [[Blaaze]] and [[Lady Kash]] with lyrics by [[Krishna Chaitanya (lyricist)|Krishna Chaitanya]] was released on 21 November 2019. The promo of the third single \"Butta Bomma\" written by Ramajogayya Sastry and sung by Armaan Malik was released on 18 December 2019, followed by the song teaser on 22 December and full song was released on 23 December 2019.\n\nThe full album was released digitally on 5 January 2020, and the songs were performed by Thaman and his musical crew at the \"AVPL Musical Concert\" held on 6 January 2020, at [[Police Ground]]s in [[Hyderabad]].\n\n{{track listing\n| headline = Track list\n| extra_column = Singer(s)\n| total_length = 25:15\n| title1 = Samajavaragamana {{small|(Male version)}}\n| lyrics1 = [[Sirivennela Seetharama Sastry]]\n| extra1 = [[Sid Sriram]]\n| length1 = 3:40\n| title2 = Ramuloo Ramulaa\n| lyrics2 = Kasarla Shyam\n| extra2 = [[Anurag Kulkarni]], [[Mangli|Mangli Satyavati]]\n| length2 = 4:06\n| title3 = OMG Daddy\n| lyrics3 = [[Krishna Chaitanya (lyricist)|Krishna Chaitanya]]\n| extra3 = [[Rahul Sipligunj]], [[Roll Rida]], [[Blaaze]], [[Lady Kash]], [[Rahul Nambiar]]\n| length3 = 3:48\n| title4 = Butta Bomma\n| lyrics4 = [[Ramajogayya Sastry]]\n| extra4 = [[Armaan Malik]]\n| length4 = 3:19\n| title5 = Samajavaragamana {{small|(Female version)}}\n| length5 = 4:01\n| title6 = Ala Vaikunthapurramuloo\n| length6 = 3:14\n| lyrics6 = Kalyan Chakravarthy\n| extra6 = [[Priya Sisters]], [[Sri Krishna]]\n| title7 = Sitharala Sirapadu\n| length7 = 3:07\n| lyrics7 = Vijay Kumar Bhalla\n| extra7 = Soorranna, Saketh Komanduri\n| title9 = \n| title10 = \n| length9 = \n| all_writing = \n| length8 = \n| title8 = \n| length10 = \n| extra5 = [[Shreya Ghoshal]]\n| lyrics5 = Sirivennela Seetharama Sastry\n}}\n\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = Angu Vaikuntapurathu\n| type         = [[Soundtrack]]\n| artist       = [[S. Thaman]]\n| cover        = \n| alt          = \n| released     = 2020\n| recorded     = 2019\n| genre        = [[Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length       = 18:02\n| language     = [[Malayalam]]\n| label        = [[Aditya Music]]\n| producer     = [[S. Thaman]]\n| prev_title   = \n| prev_year    = \n| next_title   = \n| next_year    = \n| misc         = {{Singles\n| name = Angu Vaikuntapurathu\n| type = soundtrack\n| single1 = Samajavaragamana\n| single1date = 10 November 2019\n| single2 = Aanddava Aanddava\n| single2date = 21 December 2019\n| single3 = OMG Daddy\n| single3date = 26 December 2019\n| single4 = Kutti Bomma\n| single4date = 4 January 2020\n| single5 = Itho Vaikuddapuramallo\n| single5date = 10 January 2020\n}}\n}}\nThe Malayalam versions of \"Samajavaragamana\" sung by [[Vijay Yesudas]] was released on 10 November 2019 and \"Aanddava Aanddava\" was released on 21 December 2019. The Malayalam version of \"OMG Daddy\" sung by [[Rahul Nambiar]], [[Nayana]], Shruthi Gayatri, [[Blaaze]] and penned by B. K. Harinarayanan was released on 26 December 2019.All the songs are penned by B. K. Harinarayanan.\n{{Track listing\n| all_writing =\n| title1 = Samajavaragamana {{small|(Malayalam Version)}}\n| length1 = 3:47\n| title2 = Aanddava Aanddava\n| length2 = 4:03\n| title3 = OMG Daddy {{small|(Malayalam Version)}}\n| length3 = 3:45\n| title4 = Kutti Bomma\n| length4 = 3:15\n| title5 = Itho Vaikuddapuramallo\n| length5 = 3:14\n| title6 =\n| length6 =\n| title7 =\n| length7 =\n| title8 =\n| length8 =\n| title9 =\n| length9 =\n| title10 =\n| length10 =\n| total_length =\n| extra_column = Singer(s)\n| extra1 = [[Vijay Yesudas]]\n| lyrics1 = B. K. Harinarayanan\n| extra2 = Hanuman,  Nayana\n| lyrics2 = B. K. Harinarayanan\n| extra3 = [[Rahul Nambiar]], Nayana, Shruthi Gayatri, [[Blaaze]]\n| lyrics3 = B. K. Harinarayanan\n| extra4 = Srikrishna Vishnubhotla\n| lyrics4 = B. K. Harinarayanan\n| extra5 = [[Priya Sisters]], Saketh Komanduri\n| lyrics5 = B. K. Harinarayanan\n}}\n\n== Release ==\nThe film was released on 12 January 2020 to coincide with [[Makar Sankranti|Sankranti]] and also released on 11 January 2020, in the US, a day before it's official release in India.\n\nThis film has dubbed version in [[Malayalam]], titled ''Angu Vaikuntapurathu'', and released simultaneously in [[Kerala]]. This film was also released in [[Japan]] on the same date.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.humax-cinema.co.jp/ikebukuro/news/10443/ |title=Humax Cinema Ikebukuro Event |website=indoeiga.com |url-status=live |access-date=6 January 2020 }}{{Dead link|date=January 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> \nAla Vaikuntapuram Lo was made with a budget of {{INRConvert|120|c}} It is termed to be Allu Arjun's most expensive film.\n\n===Home Media===\nThe film was made available for digital streaming via [[Netflix]] and Sun NXT on 27 February 2020, with English subtitles.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/telugu/ala-vaikunthapurramloo-now-available-on-netflix-and-sun-nxt-6288890/|title=Ala Vaikunthapurramloo now available on Netflix and Sun NXT|website=[[The Indian Express]]|accessdate=27 February 2020}}</ref> The Malayalam dubbed version was also made available on Netflix from 4 March 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.whats-on-netflix.com/coming-soon/whats-coming-to-netflix-this-week-march-2nd-march-8th/|title=What's Coming to Netflix This Week (March 2nd \u2013 March 8th)|website=Whats-on-netflix.com|accessdate=1 March 2020}}</ref> Upon the digital release, it became one of the most streamed and top trending Indian films on Netflix.{{cn|date=March 2020}}\n\n== Marketing ==\nThe team released a small behind the set's video to promote the start of films production. A small video to reveal the title of the film was released on 15 August 2019 as an Independence day treat. After unveiling the first glimpse, Allu Arjun's funny gesture made the audience and fans understood that this will be a middle-class family story with Trivikram's style of humour.<ref name=\"Title\" /> The first look poster of the film was released on 1 September 2019. It gives the 'vintage Trivikram mark for its rich appeal and classy look of Bunny'.<ref name=\":p1\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.telugu360.com/ala-vaikuntapuram-lo-first-look-poster/ |title=Ala Vaikunthapuramlo FL : AA charms in 'Trivikram' mark stylish look |date=September 2019 |website=Telugu 360 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190901054632/https://www.telugu360.com/ala-vaikuntapuram-lo-first-look-poster/ |archive-date=1 September 2019 |access-date=1 September 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe second look poster was released on 7 October 2019, coinciding with [[Vijayadashami|Dusshera]] which features Allu Arjun in an action avatar.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.myfirstshow.com/ala-vaikunthapurramloo-dussehra-poster-out/ |title=Ala Vaikunthapurramloo Dussehra Poster OUT!!while ago |date=7 October 2019 |website=Tollywood Movie News, Telugu Movie Review and Rating, Stills, News, Censor Talk - Myfirstshow |language=en-US |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191109155029/https://www.myfirstshow.com/ala-vaikunthapurramloo-dussehra-poster-out/ |archive-date=9 November 2019 |access-date=9 November 2019}}</ref> Another poster, revealing the release date was launched on 13 October 2019.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/mahesh-babu-allu-arjun-to-clash-at-the-box-office-during-sankranti/articleshow/71047902.cms |title=Mahesh Babu, Allu Arjun to clash at the box office during Sankranti? - Times of India |website=The Times of India |language=en |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191003145155/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/mahesh-babu-allu-arjun-to-clash-at-the-box-office-during-sankranti/articleshow/71047902.cms |archive-date=3 October 2019 |access-date=9 November 2019}}</ref> A new poster revealing Sushanth's character was released on 20 October 2019.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/first-look-sushanth-looks-classy-in-ala-vaikunthapurramuloo/articleshow/71687461.cms |title=First Look: Sushanth looks classy in Ala Vaikunthapurramuloo - Times of India |website=The Times of India |language=en |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191116215825/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/first-look-sushanth-looks-classy-in-ala-vaikunthapurramuloo/articleshow/71687461.cms |archive-date=16 November 2019 |access-date=9 November 2019}}</ref> Another poster from the film was released on 4 November 2019, on the occasion of Tabu's birthday.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/happy-birthday-tabu-first-look-poster-of-the-ravishing-actress-from-ala-vaikunthapurramuloo/articleshow/71887379.cms |title=Happy Birthday Tabu: First look poster of the ravishing actress from Ala Vaikunthapurramuloo - Times of India |website=The Times of India |language=en |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191109011830/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/happy-birthday-tabu-first-look-poster-of-the-ravishing-actress-from-ala-vaikunthapurramuloo/articleshow/71887379.cms |archive-date=9 November 2019 |access-date=9 November 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe first look of the Malayalam version of the film was unveiled on 7 November 2019, coinciding with director Trivikram's birthday.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://m.dailyhunt.in/News/India/English/industry+hit+english-epaper-indhiten/ala+vaikunthapurramuloo+titled+as+angu+vaikuntapurathu+in+malayalam-newsid-146064622 |title=Ala Vaikunthapurramuloo Titled As Angu Vaikuntapurathu In Malayalam - Industry Hit English |website=Dailyhunt |language=en |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191109153917/https://m.dailyhunt.in/news/india/english/industry+hit+english-epaper-indhiten/ala+vaikunthapurramuloo+titled+as+angu+vaikuntapurathu+in+malayalam-newsid-146064622 |archive-date=9 November 2019 |access-date=9 November 2019 }}</ref> The glimpse of film's teaser was released on 8 December 2019. The official teaser was released on 11 December 2019, and received positive response from audiences.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.thehansindia.com/cinema/tollywood/ala-vaikunthapurramloo-movie-teaser-to-be-out-on-december-11th-588360 |title=Ala Vaikunthapurramloo Movie teaser to be out on December 11th |last=Vyas |date=9 December 2019 |website=www.thehansindia.com |language=en |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191223044852/https://www.thehansindia.com/cinema/tollywood/ala-vaikunthapurramloo-movie-teaser-to-be-out-on-december-11th-588360 |archive-date=23 December 2019 |access-date=23 December 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.timesnownews.com/entertainment/south-gossip/article/video-ala-vaikunthapurramloo-teaser-allu-arjun-makes-a-dashing-entry-in-this-entertainer/525993 |title=[Video] Ala Vaikunthapurramloo teaser: Allu Arjun makes a dashing entry in this entertainer |website=www.timesnownews.com |language=en |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191223044853/https://www.timesnownews.com/entertainment/south-gossip/article/video-ala-vaikunthapurramloo-teaser-allu-arjun-makes-a-dashing-entry-in-this-entertainer/525993 |archive-date=23 December 2019 |access-date=23 December 2019}}</ref> The teaser of the film's Malayalam version was released on 19 December 2019. After releasing several posters in order to promote the film, the makers released the film's trailer  on 6 January 2020.{{fact|date=February 2020}}\n\n== Critical reception ==\nThe film received positive reviews especially for the performance of [[Allu Arjun]], musical score by [[S. Thaman]], and the script and screenplay penned by [[Trivikram Srinivas|Trivikram]], while the predictable storyline and the narrative of the film were criticised.\n\nHemanth Kumar of [[Firstpost]] gave the film 3.25 stars out of 5 and wrote \"[[Trivikram Srinivas]] is a wordsmith of the highest order, and when he's in great form,everything he writes is like music to the ears. He makes you want to latch on to everything that the characters speak or sing throughout the story. However, in ''Ala Vaikuntapurramlo'', he takes a detour from his path and focuses more on the emotional drama between the characters. More than the witty lines and humour, it's the depth in the emotional conversations between the characters that leave a strong impression.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/ala-vaikunthapurramuloo-movie-review-allu-arjun-murali-sharma-shine-in-trivikram-srinivas-heartfelt-drama-7895171.html |title=Allu Arjun and Murali Sharma shine in Trivikram Srinivas's heartfelt drama:Ala Vaikunthapuramuloo Review |last=Hemanth Kumar |date=12 January 2020 |website=firstpost.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200112141910/https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/ala-vaikunthapurramuloo-movie-review-allu-arjun-murali-sharma-shine-in-trivikram-srinivas-heartfelt-drama-7895171.html |archive-date=12 January 2020 |access-date=13 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nA review posted by Rohit Mohan on [[Koimoi]] said the film to be \"a perfect family entertainer to watch on this festive season of [Sankranti] with your near and dear ones, not only for Allu Arjun fans but also for every movie lovers.\" He gave the film three and a half stars out of five.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.koimoi.com/reviews/ala-vaikunthapurramloo-review-allu-arjun-trivikram-srinivass-sakranti-treat-wins-hearts/ |title=Allu Arjun and Trivikram Srinivas's Sankranthi treat wins hearts |last=Rohit Mohan |date=12 January 2020 |website=koimoi.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200112205954/https://www.koimoi.com/reviews/ala-vaikunthapurramloo-review-allu-arjun-trivikram-srinivass-sakranti-treat-wins-hearts/ |archive-date=12 January 2020 |access-date=13 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n[[The Hans India]] gave the film 3.25 stars out of 5 stating that performances, narration and bgm are the major plus points of the film while also mentioning that there are no major minus points in the movie. Trivikram Srinivas received praise for his script while Allu Arjun was praised for his performance. It was concluded that Ala Vaikunthapurramlo is definitely a worth watching movie.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.thehansindia.com/movie-reviews/ala-vaikunthapurramlo-movie-review-rating-3255-76535 |title=Ala Vaikunthapurramlo movie review & rating |last=The Hans India |date=12 January 2020 |website=thehansindia.com |access-date=13 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nNeeshita Nyayapati of [[The Times of India]] gave the film 3.5 stars out of 5 stating \"Ala Vaikunthapurramuloo has a bit of everything and despite the clich\u00e9 and the predictable storyline : Trivikram manages to make it work and deliver what he promises. Watch this for Allu Arjun, especially if you're a fan, for he shines in this one and of course, the fun of it all.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movie-reviews-ala-vaikunthapurramuloo/movie-review/73209891.cms |title=Ala Vaikunthapurramuloo has a bit of everything \u2014 there's romance, drama, comedy, emotion and lots of swag |last=Neeshita Nyayapati |date=13 January 2019 |website=indiatimes.com |access-date=14 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nKarthik Keramalu of [[The Quint]] called Ala Vaikunthapurramlo an entertainer that promises fun. According to him \"Ala Vaikunthapurramuloo has a lot going for it because Bantu (weirdest name for a Telugu movie hero) spends time with other characters (played by Tabu, Jayaram, Sunil, Sachin Khedekar, Vennela Kishore, Rajendra Prasad, Rahul Ramakrishna, Nivetha Pethuraj etc...) and doesn't wallow in mediocrity for a long time. And P. S., Vinod's cinematography makes each frame in the action episodes appear as avant-garde paintings. And on top of it all, the songs are a treat!An absolute treat!\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.thequint.com/entertainment/movie-reviews/ala-vaikunthapurramuloo-review |title=Ala Vaikunthapurramuloo is an entertainer that promises fun |last=Karthik Keramalu |date=13 January 2020 |website=thequint.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200113130852/https://www.thequint.com/entertainment/movie-reviews/ala-vaikunthapurramuloo-review |archive-date=13 January 2020 |access-date=14 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nBhavana Sharma of [[International Business Times]] called the film a \"''paisa vasool''\" entertainer with amazing performances. She further added \"Allu Arjun is back with a bang after a gap of two years. Living up to the expectations of the audiences and showing Trivikram's mark everywhere, Ala Vaikunthapurramuloo rings in the celebrations of the Sankranti festival and proves that the film was worth the wait.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://amp.ibtimes.co.in/ala-vaikunthapuramlo-review-paisa-vasool-entertainer-amazing-performances-811603 |title=Paisa Vasool entertainer with amazing performances |last=Bhavana Sharma |date=12 January 2020 |website=ibtimes.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200113214947/https://amp.ibtimes.co.in/ala-vaikunthapuramlo-review-paisa-vasool-entertainer-amazing-performances-811603 |archive-date=13 January 2020 |access-date=14 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nSangeetha Devi Dundoo of [[The Hindu]] called the film an absorbing and entertaining drama presented by Trivikram - Allu Arjun duo. She said the film hits the right notes.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/ala-vaikunthapurramuloo-review-this-trivikram-srinivas-and-allu-arjun-film-hits-the-right-notes/article30549122.ece |title=Ala Vaikunthapurramuloo film review |last=Sangeetha Devi Dundoo |date=12 January 2020 |newspaper=The Hindu |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200113175751/https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/ala-vaikunthapurramuloo-review-this-trivikram-srinivas-and-allu-arjun-film-hits-the-right-notes/article30549122.ece |archive-date=13 January 2020 |access-date=14 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb title|tt9537292}}\n{{Trivikram Srinivas}}\n\n[[Category:2020 films]]\n[[Category:Telugu-language films]]\n[[Category:2020s Telugu-language films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:Indian action drama films]]\n[[Category:Films about families]]\n[[Category:Masala films]]\n[[Category:2020s action drama films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Trivikram Srinivas]]\n[[Category:Telugu film scores by S. Thaman]]\n[[Category:Geetha Arts films]]\n[[Category:Films set in Gujarat]]\n[[Category:Films set in Paris]]\n[[Category:Films shot at Ramoji Film City]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Hyderabad, India]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Andhra Pradesh]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Gujarat]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Paris]]\n[[Category:Films shot in France]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2020 Indian Telugu-language action film}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=June 2019}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Ala Vainkunthapurramuloo\n| image          = Ala Vaikunthapurramuloo.jpeg\n| caption        = Poster\n| director       = [[Trivikram Srinivas]]\n| producer       = {{ubl| [[Allu Aravind]]|[[S. Radha Krishna|S. Radha Krishna<br /> (China Babu)]]}}\n| writer         = Trivikram Srinivas\n| starring       = {{ubl|[[Allu Arjun]]|[[Pooja Hegde]]|[[Tabu (actress)|Tabu]]|[[Jayaram]]|[[Sushanth]]|[[Navdeep]]|[[Nivetha Pethuraj]]|[[Samuthirakani]]|[[Murali Sharma]]|[[Rajendra Prasad (actor)|Rajendra Prasad]]}}\n| released       = {{Film date|df=y|2020|01|12}}\n| music          = [[S. Thaman]]\n| cinematography = [[P. S. Vinod]]\n| editing        = Navin Nooli\n| studio         = {{ubl|[[Geetha Arts]]|Haarika & Hassine Creations}}\n| runtime        = 165 minutes<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://gallery.123telugu.com/content/slideshows/2020/01/Censor-Certificate-Ala-Vaikunthapurramloo/imgpages/image000.html |title=Censor Certificate Ala Vaikunthapurramloo |website=123telugu.com}}</ref>\n| country        = India\n| language       = [[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n| budget         = {{INR|link=yes|120 [[crore]]}}<ref name=\"AVPL Budget\">{{cite\n web|url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/ala-vaikunthapurramuloo-beats-rangasthalam-lifetime-collection-worldwide-box-office-10-days-812108|title=AVPL 10 days Gross WW|date=22 January 2020|accessdate=23 January 2020}}</ref>\n| gross          = {{Estimation}} {{INR|link=yes|220 [[crore]]}}<ref name=\"AVPL Budget\" />\n}}\n\n'''''Ala Vaikunthapurramuloo''''' ({{translation|''Like that in Vaikunthapurram''}}) is a 2020 Indian [[Telugu language|Telugu]]-language [[Action film|action-drama film]]<ref name=\"british-board\">{{Cite web |url=https://bbfc.co.uk/releases/ala-vaikunthapurramuloo-film |title=ALA VAIKUNTHAPURRAMULOO |website=[[British Board of Film Classification]] |access-date=8 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.republicworld.com/entertainment-news/others/ala-vaikunthapurramuloo-starring-allu-arjun-enters-the-rs200-crore-club.html|title='Ala Vaikunthapurramuloo' Starring Allu Arjun Enters Rs 200 Crores Club Worldwide|website=[[Republic TV]]|accessdate=28 January 2020}}</ref> directed by [[Trivikram Srinivas]] and co-produced by [[Allu Aravind]] and [[S. Radha Krishna]] under their banners [[Geetha Arts]] and Haarika & Hassine Creations.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.in.com/Entertainment/regional/allu-arjuns-next-film-titled-ala-vaikunthapuramlo-and-first-glimpse-teaser-revealed-500275.htm |title=Allu Arjun's next film titled Ala Vaikuntapuramlo and first glimpse teaser revealed! |website=in.com |language=en |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200112130606/https://www.in.com/entertainment/regional/allu-arjuns-next-film-titled-ala-vaikunthapuramlo-and-first-glimpse-teaser-revealed-500275.htm |archive-date=12 January 2020 |access-date=19 August 2019}}</ref> The film features [[Allu Arjun]] and [[Pooja Hegde]] in the lead roles, while [[Tabu (actress)|Tabu]], [[Jayaram]], [[Sushanth]], [[Navdeep]], [[Nivetha Pethuraj]], [[Samuthirakani]], [[Murali Sharma]], [[Rajendra Prasad (actor)|Rajendra Prasad]], [[Sunil (actor)|Sunil]], [[Sachin Khedekar]], and  [[Harsha Vardhan]] play pivotal roles.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/amp/movies/regional-cinema/story/aa-19-allu-arjun-film-with-director-trivikram-srinivas-goes-on-floors-1501233--04-13 |title=AA 19: Allu Arjun film with director Trivikram Srinivas goes on floors |website=India Today}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.in.com/entertainment/regional/aa19-jayaram-undergoes-a-massive-transformation-for-his-next-with-allu-arjun-491955.htm |title=#AA19: Jayaram undergoes a massive transformation for his next with Allu Arjun! |website=in.com |language=en |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190819125704/https://www.in.com/entertainment/regional/aa19-jayaram-undergoes-a-massive-transformation-for-his-next-with-allu-arjun-491955.htm |archive-date=19 August 2019 |access-date=19 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/tabu-welcomed-on-board-to-trivikram-allu-arjun-pooja-hegdes-aa19/articleshow/70357457.cms |title=Tabu welcomed on-board to Trivikram, Allu Arjun, Pooja Hegde's #AA19 - Times of India |website=The Times of India |language=en |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190906045955/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/tabu-welcomed-on-board-to-trivikram-allu-arjun-pooja-hegdes-aa19/articleshow/70357457.cms |archive-date=6 September 2019 |access-date=19 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/sushanth-shares-his-shooting-experience-aa19-is-one-of-the-coolest-fun-sets-ive-been/articleshow/70409601.cms |title=Sushanth shares his shooting experience: \"AA19 is one of the coolest & fun sets I've been\" - Times of India |website=The Times of India |language=en |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190812164930/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/sushanth-shares-his-shooting-experience-aa19-is-one-of-the-coolest-fun-sets-ive-been/articleshow/70409601.cms |archive-date=12 August 2019 |access-date=19 August 2019}}</ref> The film features soundtrack composed by [[S. Thaman|Thaman S.]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/thaman-roped-score-music-allu-arjun-trivikram-film-99988 |title=Thaman roped to score music in Allu Arjun - Trivikram film |date=13 April 2019 |website=thenewsminute.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200114052127/https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/thaman-roped-score-music-allu-arjun-trivikram-film-99988 |archive-date=14 January 2020 |access-date=14 January 2020}}</ref>, while cinematography and editing were handled by [[P. S. Vinod]] and Navin Nooli respectively.\n\nThe narrative revolves around Bantu, a skilled middle-class man who is despised and is often neglected by his father Valmiki. What Bantu doesn't know is that he's actually the son of a businessman swapped by Valmiki with his own son to give the latter a comfortable life. A violent incident draws Bantu closer to the truth, upon learning which he decides to enter Vaikunthapurram, the home of his real parents and eventually confront those who threaten his family.\n\nThe film was released theatrically on 12 January 2020, coinciding with [[Makar Sankranti|Sankranti]]. It opened to positive reviews, with critics praising Allu Arjun and Murali Sharma's performances, Trivikram's writing/direction and Thaman's music. The film became a commercial success, running for more than 50 days at the domestic box office.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.filmibeat.com/telugu/news/2020/ala-vaikunthapurramloo-50-days-worldwide-collection-allu-arjun-is-2020-sankranti-winner-295599.html|title=Ala Vaikunthapurramloo 50 Days Worldwide Collection: Allu Arjun Movie Is A 2020 Sankranti Winner|website=Filmibeat.com|accessdate=1 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Spelling ==\nThe title of the film would be [[Hunterian transliteration|correctly transliterated]] as ''Ala Vaikunthapuramulo'' (or as {{transl|te|ISO|Ala Vaiku\u1e47\u1e6dhapuramul\u014d}} in the [[ISO 15919|ISO transliteration system]]) according to the [[Telugu script|Telugu source text]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Information and documentation \u2014 Transliteration of Devanagari and related Indic scripts into Latin characters |url=http://www.chatranjali.fr/Scripts/Standards/ISO15919.pdf |website=Chatranjali |publisher=International Organization for Standardization |accessdate=17 February 2020 |pages=12 |date=1 October 2001}}</ref> However, it was officially released as ''Ala Vaikunthapurramuloo'' and that spelling has thus entered into common use.<ref name=\"british-board\"/>\n\n== Plot ==\nValmiki ([[Murali Sharma]]) and Ramachandra ([[Jayaram (actor)|Jayaram]]) start their career working as clerks in the company of Ananth Radhakrishna, or ARK ([[Sachin Khedekar]]). Ramachandra falls in love with ARK\u2019s daughter Yasu ([[Tabu (actress)|Tabu]]), and becomes rich through his marriage to her in no time while Valmiki remains poor. On the day of the birth of both Valmiki\u2019s and Ramachandra\u2019s children, Ramachandra\u2019s son appears to be dead, so the nurse Sulochana ([[Easwari Rao]]) and Valmiki switch the two boys out. However, when Valmiki takes the child down, the child begins to cry and turns out to be alive. The nurse wants to switch them out again, but Valmiki prevents her from doing it and accidentally pushes her off a ledge. The nurse goes into a coma, while Valmiki gets a leg cramp that makes him limp permanently.\n\nThe boys, Raj Manohar ([[Sushanth]]) and Bantu ([[Allu Arjun]]), are raised in two different worlds. Raj is a slow, silent, young rich boy while Bantu is a smart, outspoken, hard working, middle class man. Valmiki always favors Raj no matter how hard Bantu tries to impress Valmiki. He treats Bantu with hatred and neglect due to his true parentage, even going as far as to cancel his MBA scholarship. On his way to an interview at a travel agency, Bantu\u2019s sister\u2019s scarf is pulled off by Shekhar ([[Navdeep]]). Angry, Bantu follows Shekhar and his friends and thrashes them. Ravindra ([[Rahul Ramakrishna]]) interviews Bantu and reveals that Shekhar is the agency's HR manager. Bantu apologizes to Shekhar and convinces him with his wits, successfully getting a job at the travel agency. On his first day of work, Bantu get infatuated with his boss Amulya ([[Pooja Hegde]]), and stares at her legs on the elevator, without realizing she is the CEO of the travel agency. As a result, Amulya gives Bantu some tough assignments to teach him a lesson. After a trip to Paris together, she begins to reciprocate Bantu\u2019s feelings for her. Meanwhile, Raj returns from abroad, unable to complete his MBA. Ramachandra sends Raj to reject Paidithalli ([[Govind Padmasoorya]]) who wants to buy 50% of ARK\u2019s shares. Ramachandra watches from a hotel where Amulya, Bantu, and Sudarshan ([[Brahmaji]]) have a meeting. Ramachandra is disappointed by Raj\u2019s hesitance and inability to say no to Paidithalli, but is proud of Bantu and Amulya for saying no to Sudarshan, who wanted to buy Amulya\u2019s travel agency. Due to this, ARK fixes an engagement between Raj and Amulya, but Raj was actually in love with his cousin Nandini ([[Nivetha Pethuraj]]).\n\nDue to Bantu\u2019s refusal, Sudarshan files a case against Bantu and Amulya. Amulya finally reveals her feelings for Bantu while reprimanding him for his inability to lie to others. Bantu convinces her to tell Ramachandra the truth-that she is in love with Bantu and does not want to get married to Raj. Appala Naidu ([[Samuthirakani]]), a powerful and influential man, as well as Paidithalli\u2019s father, attempts to kill Ramachandra because of the refusal moments before Amulya and Bantu arrive. Bantu saves Ramachandra and takes him to the hospital. Bantu meets Sulochana, who has come out of her coma, and learns of his true parentage. Angry, Bantu slaps Valmiki and tells him that he knows the truth about his birth. He blackmails Ramachandra\u2019s doctor, Shrinivas ([[Vennela Kishore]]) to enter Vaikuntapuram - Ramachandra's home. ARK is fond of Bantu for saving Ramachandra, fixing his relationship with Yasu, setting Paidathalli straight, and handling other business problems. \n\nDue to all this, ARK throws a huge party in happiness, where Yasu witnesses Bantu and Amulya kissing and reports it to the household. Bantu is kicked out by Valmiki and the engagement is cancelled. Appala Naidu uses this to his advantage, kidnapping Nandu and threatening to kill her unless Ramachandra signs off the shares for Paidithalli. When Valmiki begs Bantu to save Nandu, he refuses, but goes anyway. He thrashes the goons, slams Paidathalli, and stabs Appala Naidu with a kebab skewer. But later, Raj comes and saves Appala Naidu and his henchmen, thus Appala Naidu comes out of his enmity with Ramachandra by seeing Raj's humanity.\n\nWhen Bantu and Valmiki are at Vaikuntapuram, ARK slaps Valmiki and reveals that he heard the conversation between Sulochana and Bantu right before her death. Bantu is able to reunite with his biological father,  Ramachandra, but asks him not to reveal this secret to Yasu, because Yasu is still thinking that Raj is her biological son, if he says the truth, then Yasu will get depressed. However Yasu and Raj hear this conversation and Yasu agrees Bantu as his son and the family decides to give him 50% of the company\u2019s shares. Raj also accepts Valmiki as his father and stay in his house happily for 5 years or more to gain the skills necessary to become the CEO.  Valmiki struggles to accept the fact that Raj feels better suited in a middle class setting, repenting for the mistake he made 25 years ago. The film ends with Bantu going to his office as CEO with his wife Amulya in helicopter which makes Valmiki jealous.\n\n== Cast ==\n{{colbegin}}\n* [[Allu Arjun]] as Bantu / \u201cRaja\u201d as a nurse calls him\n* [[Pooja Hegde]] as Amulya / \u201cAmmu\u201d\n* [[Tabu (actress)|Tabu]] as Yasoda \u201cYasu\u201d Radhakrishna, Bantu's real mother\n* [[Jayaram]] as Ramachandra, Bantu's real father\n* [[Sushanth]] as Raj Manohar \n* [[Navdeep]] as Shekhar\n* [[Nivetha Pethuraj]] as Nandini \u201cNandu\u201d\n* [[Murali Sharma]] as Valmiki, Raj\u2019s real father\n* [[Ananth Babu]] as Pujari/ Pujari\n* [[Rohini]] as Lakshmi, Valmiki\u2019s wife\n* [[Rajendra Prasad (actor)|Rajendra Prasad]] as [[Deputy Inspector General of Police|DIG]] Govardhan Prajapati\n* [[Sachin Khedekar]] as Ananth Radhakrishna (ARK), Yasu's father\n* [[Samuthirakani]] as Appala Naidu\n* [[Sunil (actor)|Sunil]] as Sitaram \n* [[Harsha Vardhan]] as Kashiram\n* [[Govind Padmasoorya]] as Paidithalli \n* [[Rahul Ramakrishna]] as K. Ravindra Reddy\n* [[Vennela Kishore]] as Shrinivas, Ramachandra\u2019s doctor \n* [[Brahmaji]] as Sudharshan\n* [[Ajay (actor)|Ajay]] as Banginapalli Bangaram Naidu, Appala Naidu's brother-in-law  \n* [[Tanikella Bharani]] as Anjaneya Prasad, Amulya's father\n* [[Chammak Chandra]] as Chandru, money lender\n* [[Vaishnavi Chaitanya]] as Sailaja, Bantu's sister (actually Raj's sister)\n* [[Hyper Aadi]] as Rangaraju, worker in port\n* [[Brahmanandam]] in a guest appearance in the song \"Ramuloo Ramulaa\"\n* [[Easwari Rao]] as Nurse Sulochana (cameo appearance)\n{{colend}}\n\n== Production ==\n\nAfter the release of ''[[Aravinda Sametha Veera Raghava]]'', speculations arose that [[Trivikram Srinivas|Trivikram]] would direct a film with [[Allu Arjun]] which would be based on Rayalaseema factionalism and also rumors stated that jayanth will be playing a cop who will be dealing with factionalism in his own way. This project was officially confirmed but there was no clue about the genre. On the eve of new year it was officially announced by [[Geetha Arts]] that their next film will be in the direction of Trivikram and also mentioned that it is a co-production with Haarika & Hassine Creations.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/details-of-allu-arjuns-aa19-with-trivikram-srinivas/articleshow/67323091.cms |title=Details of Allu Arjun's #AA19 with Trivikram Srinivas |date=31 December 2018 |website=Times of India |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190923133417/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/details-of-allu-arjuns-aa19-with-trivikram-srinivas/articleshow/67323091.cms |archive-date=23 September 2019 |access-date=1 September 2019}}</ref> On 8 April 2019, the lead cast and crew was announced on the occasion of Allu Arjun's birthday. On 13 April 2019, the film was formally started shooting by commencing a puja ceremony attended by film team.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/allu-arjun-poses-for-a-snap-with-fans-after-aa19-puja-ceremony/amp_articleshow/68865124.cms|title=Allu Arjun poses for a snap with fans after #AA19 puja ceremony}}</ref>\n\nThe first schedule of the film started on 23 April 2019. The second schedule started on 5 June 2019, during this schedule the film added [[Pooja Hegde]], [[Nivetha Pethuraj]], [[Tabu (actress)|Tabu]] and [[Sushanth]] in pivotal roles.<ref name=\"Firstpost\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/aa19-tabu-joins-cast-of-allu-arjun-pooja-hegde-starrer-directed-by-trivikram-srinivas-7049751.html/amp |title=AA19: Tabu joins cast of Allu Arjun, Pooja Hegde-starrer, directed by Trivikram Srinivas |website=First Post |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190821102624/https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/aa19-tabu-joins-cast-of-allu-arjun-pooja-hegde-starrer-directed-by-trivikram-srinivas-7049751.html/amp |archive-date=21 August 2019 |access-date=15 August 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"IndExp\">{{Cite web |url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/telugu/sushanth-joins-the-shoot-of-aa19-5769282/lite/ |title=Sushanth joins the shoot of AA19 |website=Indian Express |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190815090130/https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/telugu/sushanth-joins-the-shoot-of-aa19-5769282/lite/ |archive-date=15 August 2019 |access-date=15 August 2019|date=7 June 2019 }}</ref> The title, ''Ala Vaikunthapurramuloo'', was revealed on 15 August 2019.<ref name=\"Title\">{{Cite web |url=https://telugu.samayam.com/telugu-movies/cinema-news/allu-arjun-19th-movie-with-trivikram-ala-vaikunthapuramulo-first-glimpse-released/amp_articleshow/70687142.cms |title=AA 19 First Glimpse: \u0c05\u0c32\u0c4d\u0c32\u0c41 \u0c05\u0c30\u0c4d\u0c1c\u0c41\u0c28\u0c4d '\u0c05\u0c32 \u0c35\u0c48\u0c15\u0c41\u0c02\u0c20\u0c2a\u0c41\u0c30\u0c2e\u0c41\u0c32\u0c4b'.. \u0c2b\u0c38\u0c4d\u0c1f\u0c4d \u0c2a\u0c02\u0c1a\u0c4d \u0c2a\u0c47\u0c32\u0c3f\u0c02\u0c26\u0c47! |website=Telugu Samayam |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190815090135/https://telugu.samayam.com/telugu-movies/cinema-news/allu-arjun-19th-movie-with-trivikram-ala-vaikunthapuramulo-first-glimpse-released/amp_articleshow/70687142.cms |archive-date=15 August 2019 |access-date=13 August 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn mid-November, the team moved to [[France]] to film the song \"Samajavaragamana\". Parts of the song was shot at [[Mont-Saint-Michel]] in [[Normandy]], [[France]], and the [[Eiffel Tower]], in [[Paris]]. The song was also filmed at [[Le Lido|Lido de Paris]], a world-famous cabaret [[theatre]], and became the first South Indian film to shoot there.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.telugucinema.com/news/allu-arjun-shoots-famous-cabaret-show |title=Allu Arjun shoots at the famous cabaret show |last=jalapathy |date=9 November 2019 |website=telugucinema.com |language=en |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191109155342/https://www.telugucinema.com/news/allu-arjun-shoots-famous-cabaret-show |archive-date=9 November 2019 |access-date=9 November 2019}}</ref> Tamil director and actor [[Samuthirakani]] was roped in to play a negative role.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/amp/entertainment/tollywood/261019/samuthirakani-as-villain.html |title=Samuthirakani as villain |website=[[Deccan Chronicle]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191025225858/https://www.deccanchronicle.com/amp/entertainment/tollywood/261019/samuthirakani-as-villain.html |archive-date=25 October 2019 |access-date=26 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Soundtrack==\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = Ala Vaikunthapurramuloo\n| type         = Soundtrack\n| artist       = [[S. Thaman|Thaman S.]]\n| cover        = \n| caption      = \n| alt          = \n| released     = 5 January 2020\n| recorded     = 2019\n| venue        = \n| studio       = \n| genre        = [[Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length       = 25:15\n| language     = [[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n| label        = [[Aditya Music]]\n| producer     = Thaman S.\n| prev_title   = [[Prati Roju Pandage]]\n| prev_year    = 2019\n| next_title   = [[Disco Raja]]\n| next_year    = 2020\n| misc         = {{Singles\n| name = Ala Vaikunthapurramuloo\n| type = soundtrack\n| single1 = Samajavaragamana {{small|(Male version)}}\n| single1date = 27 September 2019\n| single2 = Ramuloo Ramulaa\n| single2date = 25 October 2019\n| single3 = OMG Daddy\n| single3date = 21 November 2019\n| single4 = Butta Bomma\n| single4date = 23 December 2019\n| single5 = Samajavaragamana {{small|(Female version)}}\n| single5date = 3 January 2020\n| single6 = Ala Vaikunthapurramuloo\n| single6date = 6 January 2020\n| single7 = Sitharala Sirapadu\n| single7date = 17 January 2020\n}}\n}}\nThe music was composed by [[S. Thaman|Thaman S.]], marking his second collaboration with director Trivikram, after ''[[Aravinda Sametha Veera Raghava]]'' and the director's third collaboration with Allu Arjun.\n\nA glimpse of the first single \"Samajavaragamana\" featuring [[Sid Sriram]]'s voiceover, was released in all social media platforms on 25 September 2019. A minute video featuring Thaman S. and lyricist [[Sirivennela Seetharama Sastry]], who penned the lyrics for the song, who shared their opinions about the song was released later in media platforms. The full song was released on 27 September 2019 and went viral within an hour of its launch. Rather than the usual lyrical video, the YouTube video had a band, including singer Sid Sriram and composer Thaman S., performing the song on a flashy stage with shots of Pooja Hegde and Allu Arjun, and others, from the film. On 1 December 2019, it became the fastest Telugu song to 100 million views on YouTube, less than two weeks after it became the first Telugu song to hit 1 million likes on YouTube.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/Allu-Arjun-sets-new-record-avpl-1st-song-samajavaragamana-crossing-100-million-views-809673 |title=Allu Arjun sets new record with AVPL 1st song Samajavaragamana crossing 100 million views |last=Hooli |first=Shekhar |website=International Business Times |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191202144439/https://www.ibtimes.co.in/allu-arjun-sets-new-record-avpl-1st-song-samajavaragamana-crossing-100-million-views-809673 |archive-date=2 December 2019 |access-date=2 December 2019}}</ref> The female version of the song sung by Shreya Ghoshal was released on 3 January 2020.\n\nThe song teaser of the second single \"Ramuloo Ramulaa\" was released on 21 October 2019. The lyrics for the song written by Kasarla Shyam and sung by [[Anurag Kulkarni]] and [[Mangli|Mangli Satyavati]]. The single was released on 25 October 2019, with the occasion of [[Diwali]]. The YouTube video included lyrics, footage of the musicians, an Allu Arjun voice-over,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://naa-songs.download/ala-vaikuntapuramlo |title=Allu Arjun is all set to give a voice-over for 'Ramuloo Ramulaa' from his film Ala Vaikuntapuramulo |date=5 October 2019 |website=Naa songs |language=en-US |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191027095902/https://naa-songs.download/ala-vaikuntapuramlo |archive-date=27 October 2019 |access-date=27 October 2019}}</ref> clips of the actual dance number from the movie, behind the scenes footage, and members of the cast wishing fans a happy Diwali at the end.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wFAj0pW6xX0&list=RDwFAj0pW6xX0&start_radio=1 |title=Ramuloo Ramulaa Full Song |website=YouTube |access-date=27 October 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe song teaser of the third single \"OMG Daddy\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://moviesupdates.in/ala-vaikunthapurramuloo-omg-daddy-song-teaser/ |title=Ala Vaikunthapurramuloo \u2013 OMG Daddy Song Teaser |date=1 January 2018}}</ref> was released on 14 November 2019, as a [[Children's Day]] treats from the team. The teaser features Allu Arha and Allu Ayaan, the children of Allu Arjun. The song performed by [[Rahul Sipligunj]], [[Rahul Nambiar]], [[Roll Rida]], [[Blaaze]] and [[Lady Kash]] with lyrics by [[Krishna Chaitanya (lyricist)|Krishna Chaitanya]] was released on 21 November 2019. The promo of the third single \"Butta Bomma\" written by Ramajogayya Sastry and sung by Armaan Malik was released on 18 December 2019, followed by the song teaser on 22 December and full song was released on 23 December 2019.\n\nThe full album was released digitally on 5 January 2020, and the songs were performed by Thaman and his musical crew at the \"AVPL Musical Concert\" held on 6 January 2020, at [[Police Ground]]s in [[Hyderabad]].\n\n{{track listing\n| headline = Track list\n| extra_column = Singer(s)\n| total_length = 25:15\n| title1 = Samajavaragamana {{small|(Male version)}}\n| lyrics1 = [[Sirivennela Seetharama Sastry]]\n| extra1 = [[Sid Sriram]]\n| length1 = 3:40\n| title2 = Ramuloo Ramulaa\n| lyrics2 = Kasarla Shyam\n| extra2 = [[Anurag Kulkarni]], [[Mangli|Mangli Satyavati]]\n| length2 = 4:06\n| title3 = OMG Daddy\n| lyrics3 = [[Krishna Chaitanya (lyricist)|Krishna Chaitanya]]\n| extra3 = [[Rahul Sipligunj]], [[Roll Rida]], [[Blaaze]], [[Lady Kash]], [[Rahul Nambiar]]\n| length3 = 3:48\n| title4 = Butta Bomma\n| lyrics4 = [[Ramajogayya Sastry]]\n| extra4 = [[Armaan Malik]]\n| length4 = 3:19\n| title5 = Samajavaragamana {{small|(Female version)}}\n| length5 = 4:01\n| title6 = Ala Vaikunthapurramuloo\n| length6 = 3:14\n| lyrics6 = Kalyan Chakravarthy\n| extra6 = [[Priya Sisters]], [[Sri Krishna]]\n| title7 = Sitharala Sirapadu\n| length7 = 3:07\n| lyrics7 = Vijay Kumar Bhalla\n| extra7 = Soorranna, Saketh Komanduri\n| title9 = \n| title10 = \n| length9 = \n| all_writing = \n| length8 = \n| title8 = \n| length10 = \n| extra5 = [[Shreya Ghoshal]]\n| lyrics5 = Sirivennela Seetharama Sastry\n}}\n\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = Angu Vaikuntapurathu\n| type         = [[Soundtrack]]\n| artist       = [[S. Thaman]]\n| cover        = \n| alt          = \n| released     = 2020\n| recorded     = 2019\n| genre        = [[Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length       = 18:02\n| language     = [[Malayalam]]\n| label        = [[Aditya Music]]\n| producer     = [[S. Thaman]]\n| prev_title   = \n| prev_year    = \n| next_title   = \n| next_year    = \n| misc         = {{Singles\n| name = Angu Vaikuntapurathu\n| type = soundtrack\n| single1 = Samajavaragamana\n| single1date = 10 November 2019\n| single2 = Aanddava Aanddava\n| single2date = 21 December 2019\n| single3 = OMG Daddy\n| single3date = 26 December 2019\n| single4 = Kutti Bomma\n| single4date = 4 January 2020\n| single5 = Itho Vaikuddapuramallo\n| single5date = 10 January 2020\n}}\n}}\nThe Malayalam versions of \"Samajavaragamana\" sung by [[Vijay Yesudas]] was released on 10 November 2019 and \"Aanddava Aanddava\" was released on 21 December 2019. The Malayalam version of \"OMG Daddy\" sung by [[Rahul Nambiar]], [[Nayana]], Shruthi Gayatri, [[Blaaze]] and penned by B. K. Harinarayanan was released on 26 December 2019.All the songs are penned by B. K. Harinarayanan.\n{{Track listing\n| all_writing =\n| title1 = Samajavaragamana {{small|(Malayalam Version)}}\n| length1 = 3:47\n| title2 = Aanddava Aanddava\n| length2 = 4:03\n| title3 = OMG Daddy {{small|(Malayalam Version)}}\n| length3 = 3:45\n| title4 = Kutti Bomma\n| length4 = 3:15\n| title5 = Itho Vaikuddapuramallo\n| length5 = 3:14\n| title6 =\n| length6 =\n| title7 =\n| length7 =\n| title8 =\n| length8 =\n| title9 =\n| length9 =\n| title10 =\n| length10 =\n| total_length =\n| extra_column = Singer(s)\n| extra1 = [[Vijay Yesudas]]\n| lyrics1 = B. K. Harinarayanan\n| extra2 = Hanuman,  Nayana\n| lyrics2 = B. K. Harinarayanan\n| extra3 = [[Rahul Nambiar]], Nayana, Shruthi Gayatri, [[Blaaze]]\n| lyrics3 = B. K. Harinarayanan\n| extra4 = Srikrishna Vishnubhotla\n| lyrics4 = B. K. Harinarayanan\n| extra5 = [[Priya Sisters]], Saketh Komanduri\n| lyrics5 = B. K. Harinarayanan\n}}\n\n== Release ==\nThe film was released on 12 January 2020 to coincide with [[Makar Sankranti|Sankranti]] and also released on 11 January 2020, in the US, a day before it's official release in India.\n\nThis film has dubbed version in [[Malayalam]], titled ''Angu Vaikuntapurathu'', and released simultaneously in [[Kerala]]. This film was also released in [[Japan]] on the same date.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.humax-cinema.co.jp/ikebukuro/news/10443/ |title=Humax Cinema Ikebukuro Event |website=indoeiga.com |url-status=live |access-date=6 January 2020 }}{{Dead link|date=January 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> \nAla Vaikuntapuram Lo was made with a budget of {{INRConvert|120|c}} It is termed to be Allu Arjun's most expensive film.\n\n===Home Media===\nThe film was made available for digital streaming via [[Netflix]] and Sun NXT on 27 February 2020, with English subtitles.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/telugu/ala-vaikunthapurramloo-now-available-on-netflix-and-sun-nxt-6288890/|title=Ala Vaikunthapurramloo now available on Netflix and Sun NXT|website=[[The Indian Express]]|accessdate=27 February 2020}}</ref> The Malayalam dubbed version was also made available on Netflix from 4 March 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.whats-on-netflix.com/coming-soon/whats-coming-to-netflix-this-week-march-2nd-march-8th/|title=What's Coming to Netflix This Week (March 2nd \u2013 March 8th)|website=Whats-on-netflix.com|accessdate=1 March 2020}}</ref> Upon the digital release, it became one of the most streamed and top trending Indian films on Netflix.{{cn|date=March 2020}}\n\n== Marketing ==\nThe team released a small behind the set's video to promote the start of films production. A small video to reveal the title of the film was released on 15 August 2019 as an Independence day treat. After unveiling the first glimpse, Allu Arjun's funny gesture made the audience and fans understood that this will be a middle-class family story with Trivikram's style of humour.<ref name=\"Title\" /> The first look poster of the film was released on 1 September 2019. It gives the 'vintage Trivikram mark for its rich appeal and classy look of Bunny'.<ref name=\":p1\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.telugu360.com/ala-vaikuntapuram-lo-first-look-poster/ |title=Ala Vaikunthapuramlo FL : AA charms in 'Trivikram' mark stylish look |date=September 2019 |website=Telugu 360 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190901054632/https://www.telugu360.com/ala-vaikuntapuram-lo-first-look-poster/ |archive-date=1 September 2019 |access-date=1 September 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe second look poster was released on 7 October 2019, coinciding with [[Vijayadashami|Dusshera]] which features Allu Arjun in an action avatar.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.myfirstshow.com/ala-vaikunthapurramloo-dussehra-poster-out/ |title=Ala Vaikunthapurramloo Dussehra Poster OUT!!while ago |date=7 October 2019 |website=Tollywood Movie News, Telugu Movie Review and Rating, Stills, News, Censor Talk - Myfirstshow |language=en-US |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191109155029/https://www.myfirstshow.com/ala-vaikunthapurramloo-dussehra-poster-out/ |archive-date=9 November 2019 |access-date=9 November 2019}}</ref> Another poster, revealing the release date was launched on 13 October 2019.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/mahesh-babu-allu-arjun-to-clash-at-the-box-office-during-sankranti/articleshow/71047902.cms |title=Mahesh Babu, Allu Arjun to clash at the box office during Sankranti? - Times of India |website=The Times of India |language=en |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191003145155/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/mahesh-babu-allu-arjun-to-clash-at-the-box-office-during-sankranti/articleshow/71047902.cms |archive-date=3 October 2019 |access-date=9 November 2019}}</ref> A new poster revealing Sushanth's character was released on 20 October 2019.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/first-look-sushanth-looks-classy-in-ala-vaikunthapurramuloo/articleshow/71687461.cms |title=First Look: Sushanth looks classy in Ala Vaikunthapurramuloo - Times of India |website=The Times of India |language=en |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191116215825/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/first-look-sushanth-looks-classy-in-ala-vaikunthapurramuloo/articleshow/71687461.cms |archive-date=16 November 2019 |access-date=9 November 2019}}</ref> Another poster from the film was released on 4 November 2019, on the occasion of Tabu's birthday.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/happy-birthday-tabu-first-look-poster-of-the-ravishing-actress-from-ala-vaikunthapurramuloo/articleshow/71887379.cms |title=Happy Birthday Tabu: First look poster of the ravishing actress from Ala Vaikunthapurramuloo - Times of India |website=The Times of India |language=en |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191109011830/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/happy-birthday-tabu-first-look-poster-of-the-ravishing-actress-from-ala-vaikunthapurramuloo/articleshow/71887379.cms |archive-date=9 November 2019 |access-date=9 November 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe first look of the Malayalam version of the film was unveiled on 7 November 2019, coinciding with director Trivikram's birthday.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://m.dailyhunt.in/News/India/English/industry+hit+english-epaper-indhiten/ala+vaikunthapurramuloo+titled+as+angu+vaikuntapurathu+in+malayalam-newsid-146064622 |title=Ala Vaikunthapurramuloo Titled As Angu Vaikuntapurathu In Malayalam - Industry Hit English |website=Dailyhunt |language=en |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191109153917/https://m.dailyhunt.in/news/india/english/industry+hit+english-epaper-indhiten/ala+vaikunthapurramuloo+titled+as+angu+vaikuntapurathu+in+malayalam-newsid-146064622 |archive-date=9 November 2019 |access-date=9 November 2019 }}</ref> The glimpse of film's teaser was released on 8 December 2019. The official teaser was released on 11 December 2019, and received positive response from audiences.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.thehansindia.com/cinema/tollywood/ala-vaikunthapurramloo-movie-teaser-to-be-out-on-december-11th-588360 |title=Ala Vaikunthapurramloo Movie teaser to be out on December 11th |last=Vyas |date=9 December 2019 |website=www.thehansindia.com |language=en |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191223044852/https://www.thehansindia.com/cinema/tollywood/ala-vaikunthapurramloo-movie-teaser-to-be-out-on-december-11th-588360 |archive-date=23 December 2019 |access-date=23 December 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.timesnownews.com/entertainment/south-gossip/article/video-ala-vaikunthapurramloo-teaser-allu-arjun-makes-a-dashing-entry-in-this-entertainer/525993 |title=[Video] Ala Vaikunthapurramloo teaser: Allu Arjun makes a dashing entry in this entertainer |website=www.timesnownews.com |language=en |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191223044853/https://www.timesnownews.com/entertainment/south-gossip/article/video-ala-vaikunthapurramloo-teaser-allu-arjun-makes-a-dashing-entry-in-this-entertainer/525993 |archive-date=23 December 2019 |access-date=23 December 2019}}</ref> The teaser of the film's Malayalam version was released on 19 December 2019. After releasing several posters in order to promote the film, the makers released the film's trailer  on 6 January 2020.{{fact|date=February 2020}}\n\n== Critical reception ==\nThe film received positive reviews especially for the performance of [[Allu Arjun]], musical score by [[S. Thaman]], and the script and screenplay penned by [[Trivikram Srinivas|Trivikram]], while the predictable storyline and the narrative of the film were criticised.\n\nHemanth Kumar of [[Firstpost]] gave the film 3.25 stars out of 5 and wrote \"[[Trivikram Srinivas]] is a wordsmith of the highest order, and when he's in great form,everything he writes is like music to the ears. He makes you want to latch on to everything that the characters speak or sing throughout the story. However, in ''Ala Vaikuntapurramlo'', he takes a detour from his path and focuses more on the emotional drama between the characters. More than the witty lines and humour, it's the depth in the emotional conversations between the characters that leave a strong impression.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/ala-vaikunthapurramuloo-movie-review-allu-arjun-murali-sharma-shine-in-trivikram-srinivas-heartfelt-drama-7895171.html |title=Allu Arjun and Murali Sharma shine in Trivikram Srinivas's heartfelt drama:Ala Vaikunthapuramuloo Review |last=Hemanth Kumar |date=12 January 2020 |website=firstpost.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200112141910/https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/ala-vaikunthapurramuloo-movie-review-allu-arjun-murali-sharma-shine-in-trivikram-srinivas-heartfelt-drama-7895171.html |archive-date=12 January 2020 |access-date=13 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nA review posted by Rohit Mohan on [[Koimoi]] said the film to be \"a perfect family entertainer to watch on this festive season of [Sankranti] with your near and dear ones, not only for Allu Arjun fans but also for every movie lovers.\" He gave the film three and a half stars out of five.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.koimoi.com/reviews/ala-vaikunthapurramloo-review-allu-arjun-trivikram-srinivass-sakranti-treat-wins-hearts/ |title=Allu Arjun and Trivikram Srinivas's Sankranthi treat wins hearts |last=Rohit Mohan |date=12 January 2020 |website=koimoi.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200112205954/https://www.koimoi.com/reviews/ala-vaikunthapurramloo-review-allu-arjun-trivikram-srinivass-sakranti-treat-wins-hearts/ |archive-date=12 January 2020 |access-date=13 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n[[The Hans India]] gave the film 3.25 stars out of 5 stating that performances, narration and bgm are the major plus points of the film while also mentioning that there are no major minus points in the movie. Trivikram Srinivas received praise for his script while Allu Arjun was praised for his performance. It was concluded that Ala Vaikunthapurramlo is definitely a worth watching movie.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.thehansindia.com/movie-reviews/ala-vaikunthapurramlo-movie-review-rating-3255-76535 |title=Ala Vaikunthapurramlo movie review & rating |last=The Hans India |date=12 January 2020 |website=thehansindia.com |access-date=13 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nNeeshita Nyayapati of [[The Times of India]] gave the film 3.5 stars out of 5 stating \"Ala Vaikunthapurramuloo has a bit of everything and despite the clich\u00e9 and the predictable storyline : Trivikram manages to make it work and deliver what he promises. Watch this for Allu Arjun, especially if you're a fan, for he shines in this one and of course, the fun of it all.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movie-reviews-ala-vaikunthapurramuloo/movie-review/73209891.cms |title=Ala Vaikunthapurramuloo has a bit of everything \u2014 there's romance, drama, comedy, emotion and lots of swag |last=Neeshita Nyayapati |date=13 January 2019 |website=indiatimes.com |access-date=14 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nKarthik Keramalu of [[The Quint]] called Ala Vaikunthapurramlo an entertainer that promises fun. According to him \"Ala Vaikunthapurramuloo has a lot going for it because Bantu (weirdest name for a Telugu movie hero) spends time with other characters (played by Tabu, Jayaram, Sunil, Sachin Khedekar, Vennela Kishore, Rajendra Prasad, Rahul Ramakrishna, Nivetha Pethuraj etc...) and doesn't wallow in mediocrity for a long time. And P. S., Vinod's cinematography makes each frame in the action episodes appear as avant-garde paintings. And on top of it all, the songs are a treat!An absolute treat!\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.thequint.com/entertainment/movie-reviews/ala-vaikunthapurramuloo-review |title=Ala Vaikunthapurramuloo is an entertainer that promises fun |last=Karthik Keramalu |date=13 January 2020 |website=thequint.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200113130852/https://www.thequint.com/entertainment/movie-reviews/ala-vaikunthapurramuloo-review |archive-date=13 January 2020 |access-date=14 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nBhavana Sharma of [[International Business Times]] called the film a \"''paisa vasool''\" entertainer with amazing performances. She further added \"Allu Arjun is back with a bang after a gap of two years. Living up to the expectations of the audiences and showing Trivikram's mark everywhere, Ala Vaikunthapurramuloo rings in the celebrations of the Sankranti festival and proves that the film was worth the wait.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://amp.ibtimes.co.in/ala-vaikunthapuramlo-review-paisa-vasool-entertainer-amazing-performances-811603 |title=Paisa Vasool entertainer with amazing performances |last=Bhavana Sharma |date=12 January 2020 |website=ibtimes.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200113214947/https://amp.ibtimes.co.in/ala-vaikunthapuramlo-review-paisa-vasool-entertainer-amazing-performances-811603 |archive-date=13 January 2020 |access-date=14 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nSangeetha Devi Dundoo of [[The Hindu]] called the film an absorbing and entertaining drama presented by Trivikram - Allu Arjun duo. She said the film hits the right notes.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/ala-vaikunthapurramuloo-review-this-trivikram-srinivas-and-allu-arjun-film-hits-the-right-notes/article30549122.ece |title=Ala Vaikunthapurramuloo film review |last=Sangeetha Devi Dundoo |date=12 January 2020 |newspaper=The Hindu |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200113175751/https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/ala-vaikunthapurramuloo-review-this-trivikram-srinivas-and-allu-arjun-film-hits-the-right-notes/article30549122.ece |archive-date=13 January 2020 |access-date=14 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb title|tt9537292}}\n{{Trivikram Srinivas}}\n\n[[Category:2020 films]]\n[[Category:Telugu-language films]]\n[[Category:2020s Telugu-language films]]\n[[