{"title_page": "OMG \u2013 Oh My God!", "text_new": "{{short description|2012 film directed by Umesh Shukla}}\n{{Other uses|Oh My God (disambiguation){{!}}Oh My God}}\n{{Distinguish|Oh, My God (2008 film)}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2013}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=May 2013}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = OMG \u2013 Oh My God!\n| image          = OMG Poster.png\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Umesh Shukla]]<ref name=\"cast\" />\n| producer       = [[Paresh Rawal]]<br>[[Akshay Kumar]]<br>[[Ashvini Yardi]]\n| writer         = Will Umesh Shukla\n| based on       = ''\"Kanji Virrudh Kanji\"''<ref>{{cite news|url=https://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/bollywood/akshay-waiting-for-twinkle-to-see-oh-my-god_120487.html|title=Akshay waiting for Twinkle to see 'Oh My God'|newspaper=[[The Times of India]]|accessdate=9 October 2012|date=6 October 2012}}</ref>\n| starring       = [[Paresh Rawal]]<br>[[Akshay Kumar]]<br>[[Mithun Chakraborty]]\n| music          = '''Score:'''<br>[[Amar Mohile]]<br>'''Songs:'''<br>[[Himesh Reshammiya]]<br>[[Sachin-Jigar]]<br>[[Meet Bros|Meet Bros. Anjjan]]\n| cinematography = [[Sethu Sriram]]\n| editing        = Tushar Shivan<br/>Rajesh Panchal\n| studio         = [[Grazing Goat Pictures Pvt. Ltd|Grazing Goat Pictures]]<br>[[Wave Group|Wave Cinemas]]<br>Spice Studios\n| distributor    = [[Viacom 18 Motion Pictures]]\n| released       = {{Film date|df=yes|2012|9|28}}\n| runtime        = 130 minutes<ref name=\"Runtime\">{{cite web|title=OMG - OH MY GOD! (PG) - British Board of Film Classification|url=http://www.bbfc.co.uk/releases/omg-oh-my-god-2012-0|publisher=[[British Board of Film Classification]]|accessdate=24 October 2012|date=19 September 2012}}</ref>\n| country        = India\n| language       = Hindi\n| budget         = {{INR}}200 million\n<ref>https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/oh-my-god-the-film-is-a-hit/story-CyGWSR6qRQowIi1b0DS8OL.html</ref>\n| gross          = {{INR}}1.81 billion\n<ref>{{cite web|url=http://boxofficeindia.com/Star_Cast/actor_record_world_total/akshay_kumar/actor |title=Archived copy |accessdate=5 September 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150804025031/http://boxofficeindia.com/Star_Cast/actor_record_world_total/akshay_kumar/actor |archivedate=4 August 2015 }}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''OMG \u2013 Oh My God!''''' is a 2012 Indian [[Hindi]]-language [[Satire|satirical]] comedy drama film which is an official remake of the 2001 Australian film ''[[The Man Who Sued God]]''. The storyline is based on a [[Gujarati language|Gujarati]] stage-play entitled ''Kanji Virudh Kanji.'' It is directed by [[Umesh Shukla]]. The film features [[Paresh Rawal]] and [[Akshay Kumar]] in the lead roles, along with [[Mithun Chakraborty]], [[Om Puri]], [[Govind Namdeo]], [[Nikhil Ratnaparkhi]], [[Poonam Jhawer]], [[Puja Gupta (actress)|Puja Gupta]] and [[Mahesh Manjrekar]] in the pivotal roles.<ref name=\"release\">{{cite web|title=The underlying message of Khiladi Kumar\u2019s forthcoming comedy|url=http://www.bollywoodlife.com/news-gossip/how-did-omg-oh-my-god-change-akshay-kumar/|publisher=Bollywood Life|date=17 September 2012|accessdate=7 October 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121006110935/http://www.bollywoodlife.com/news-gossip/how-did-omg-oh-my-god-change-akshay-kumar/|url-status=live|archivedate=6 October 2012|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Made on a budget of {{INRConvert|20|c|nolink=yes}}, the film released on 28 September 2012 to critical acclaim.<ref name=\"Budget\">{{cite web|title=Oh my God, the film is a hit!|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Bollywood/Oh-my-God-the-film-is-a-hit/Article1-938714.aspx|newspaper=[[Hindustan Times]]|accessdate=2 October 2012|date=2 October 2012|author=Shalvi Mangaokar|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131103232846/http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Bollywood/Oh-my-God-the-film-is-a-hit/Article1-938714.aspx|url-status=live|archivedate=3 November 2013|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"review\">{{cite web|title=OMG (OH MY GOD) movie review|url=http://www.reviewgang.com/movies/322-OMG-Oh-My-God-movie-review|publisher=Review Gang|accessdate=15 October 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121015090218/http://www.reviewgang.com/movies/322-OMG-Oh-My-God-movie-review|url-status=live|archivedate=15 October 2012|df=dmy-all}}</ref> The film was remade in Telugu as ''[[Gopala Gopala (2015 film)|Gopala Gopala]]'' in 2015 with [[Daggubati Venkatesh|Venkatesh]] and [[Pawan Kalyan]] in the lead roles and in Kannada with [[Upendra (actor)|Upendra]] and [[Sudeep]] titled as ''[[Mukunda Murari]] in 2016''.\n\n==Plot==\nKanji Lalji Mehta ([[Paresh Rawal]]), a middle-class [[atheism in Hinduism|atheist Hindu]] owns a shop of Hindu idols and antiques in [[Mumbai]]. He makes fun of religious activities around him and one such day, a low-intensity earthquake hits the city, and Kanji's shop is the only shop that is destroyed. His family and friends blame this on his atheism.\n\nAt the insurance office, Kanji learns that the disaster claim does not cover any damage caused by natural calamities classified under \"[[Act of God]]\". Running out of options, he decides to sue God but fails to find a lawyer for such a lawsuit. Hanif Qureshi ([[Om Puri]]), a poor Muslim lawyer, helps him file the case after Kanji decides to fight on his own. Legal notices are sent to the insurance company as well as to religious priests, Siddheshwar Maharaj, Gopi Maiyya, and their group's founder, Leeladhar Swamy ([[Mithun Chakraborty]]), summoning them to court as representatives of God.\n\nAs the court case commences and gains traction for its bizarre quality, Kanji finds himself facing armed fundamentalists and harassment, with his mortgage bank occupying the house, and his wife and kids leaving him. He is rescued from all of this by Krishna Vasudev Yadav ([[Akshay Kumar]]), who claims to be a real estate agent originally from [[Gokul]], [[Uttar Pradesh]], but appears to do fantastical tricks not possible for a human.\n\nThe lawsuit causes a public outcry. On Krishna's advice, Kanji goes to the media and gets wide coverage. Many people in a similar situation join him in the lawsuit, causing the amount of claims to skyrocket and [[Catholicism|Catholic]] priests and Muslim [[Mullah]]s to also be summoned as defendants. When the court demands written proof that the earthquake was an 'Act of God,' Krishna steers Kanji toward holy books like [[Bhagavad Gita]], [[The Quran]] and [[The Bible]]. Kanji reads them and finds a passage in each that says the world and all that happen in it, from beginning to end, is a creation of God and comes from God's will alone. This strengthens his case and increases public support. However, Kanji suffers a stroke in court and is rushed to the hospital where he goes into a coma and is paralyzed. When he opens his eyes after a month, he finds Krishna, who reveals that he is God, and proves it by curing Kanji completely. He further reveals that He created the entire world, animals and humans but not any religion, and he was the one who destroyed Kanji's shop because he wanted to punish the godmen who showed his fear to public, to earn money when in fact, He wants his creations to love him. He figured out that Kanji would end up exposing them if he destroys his Shop. \n\nKanji learns that the lawsuit's verdict was in his favor and religious organizations were ordered by court to pay the compensation to all the plaintiffs; people have begun revering Kanji himself as a god. Leeladhar, Gopi Maiyya, and Siddheshwar have taken advantage of this by opening a temple dedicated to Kanji and accumulating millions in donations. Krishna explains to Kanji that his job as God is to show people right and wrong - people do with it what they will. Kanji decides to fight back. He breaks his own statue, admonishing the crowd about trusting in God-men. He advises them to search for God in themselves and in others, not in statues; that God is everywhere, not just in temples, and faith should come from within. He tells them not to believe in fraudulent God-men, as their job is to turn religion into business.\n\nKrishna looks on proudly as Kanji speaks, then vanishes when Kanji tries to reach him after. Kanji is reunited with his family and sees Krishna's key chain on the ground. When he is about to keep it, he hears Krishna's voice, telling him to get rid of the key chain as fear of God and reliance on religious objects was what he'd fought against all this time. Kanji smiles and throws it away, watching as it disappears in the sky with a flash.<ref name=cast>{{cite web|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/cast/id/549384|title=OMG Oh My God! Cast & Crew|publisher=Bollywood Hungama|accessdate=10 October 2012|author=Taran Adarsh|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121010052818/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/cast/id/549384|archivedate=10 October 2012|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n{{div col begin}}\n*[[Paresh Rawal]] as Kanji Lalji Mehta\n*[[Akshay Kumar]] as Krishna Vasudev Yadav / [[Lord Krishna]]\n*[[Mithun Chakraborty]] as Leeladhar Swamy\n*[[Govind Namdeo]] as Siddheshwar Maharaj\n*[[Poonam Jhawer]] as Gopi Maiyya\n*[[Om Puri]] as Advocate Hanif Qureshi\n*[[Mahesh Manjrekar]] as Advocate Sardesai\n*[[Puja Gupta (actress)|Puja Gupta]] as Hanif's Daughter\n*Yousuf Hussain Khan as Judge\n*[[Lubna Salim]] as Susheela (Kanji's wife)\n*[[Nidhi Subbaiah]] as Shweta Tiwari (News reporter)\n*[[Murli Sharma]] as Laxman Mishra\n*[[Tisca Chopra]] as The interview host\n*Bhanu Prasad as The Pujari\n*[[Ishita Vyas]] Manju Vyas as The Sardesai's assistant\n*Nikhil Ratnaparkhi as Mahadev\n*[[Arun Bali]] as Accha Sadhu\n*Jaineeraj Rajpurohit as Dinesh Gandhi\n*[[Apoorva Arora]] as Jigna (Kanji's daughter)\n*Azaan Rustam Shah as Chintu (Kanji's son)\n*[[Honey Chhaya]] as Jagdishbhai\n*Manu Narula as Krishna\n*Gopal Pathak\n*[[Prabhu Deva]] in a special appearance in the song \"Go Go Go Govinda\"\n*[[Sonakshi Sinha]] in a special appearance in the song \"Go Go Go Govinda\"\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Production==\nProducer [[Akshay Kumar]] announced the film in 2012. [[Paresh Rawal]] who appeared in the original play ''Kishen vs Kanhaiya'' was cast in the lead role with Akshay Kumar playing the role of Krishna in the movie.<ref name=\"cast\"/> [[Mithun Chakraborty]] played a supporting role in the film. The filming was reported to have begun in January 2012.<ref name=appearance>{{cite news|title=Special appearance in 'OMG'|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-07-29/news-interviews/32923154_1_prabhu|accessdate=7 October 2012|newspaper=[[The Times of India]]|date=29 Jul 2012}} {{Dead link|date=October 2014}}</ref> Director [[Prabhu Deva]] appeared in an item-number along with [[Sonakshi Sinha]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/salman-khan-vs-srk-in-akshay-kumars-oh-my-god/236322-8-66.html|publisher=[[IBN Live]]|title=Akshay and Paresh together again?|date=2 January 2012|accessdate=21 March 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120307204836/http://ibnlive.in.com/news/salman-khan-vs-srk-in-akshay-kumars-oh-my-god/236322-8-66.html|archivedate=7 March 2012|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n==Soundtrack==\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = OMG \u2013 Oh My God!\n| type         = Soundtrack\n| artist       = [[Himesh Reshammiya]], [[Sachin - Jigar]] and [[Meet Bros Anjjan]]\n| cover        = \n| alt          = \n| released     = 12 September 2012\n| recorded     = \n| venue        = \n| studio       = \n| genre        = [[Film soundtrack|Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length       = \n| label        = [[T-Series (company)|T-Series]]\n| producer     = [[Himesh Reshammiya]]<br>[[Sachin - Jigar]]<br>[[Meet Bros Anjjan]]\n| prev_title   = \n| prev_year    = \n| next_title   = \n| next_year    = \n}}\n\nThe soundtrack of ''OMG \u2013 Oh My God!'' is composed by [[Himesh Reshammiya]], [[Sachin - Jigar]] and [[Meet Bros Anjjan]], whilst the lyrics have been penned by [[Shabbir Ahmed (lyricist)|Shabbir Ahmed]], [[Kumaar]], [[Swanand Kirkire]] and Subrat Sinha. The album features vocals by Reshammiya, [[Shreya Ghoshal]], [[Kailash Kher]], [[Benny Dayal]], [[Ash King]], [[Suraj Jagan]], [[Keerthi Sagathia]], [[Zubeen Garg]], [[Meet Bros Anjjan]], Arya Acharya, Mohd Irfan, [[Aman Trikha]] and Parash Nath. The full audio album was launched on 12 September 2012 by [[T-Series (company)|T-Series]].\n\n{{Track listing\n| extra_column = Singer(s)\n| all_lyrics = \n| title1 = Don't Worry (Hey Ram)\n| extra1 = Himesh Reshammiya, Benny Dayal, Arya Acharya\n| lyrics1 = [[Shabbir Ahmed (lyricist)|Shabbir Ahmed]]\n| music1 = Himesh Reshammiya\n| length1 = 05:04\n| title2 = Mere Nishaan\n| extra2 = [[Kailash Kher]], Meet Bros Anjjan\n| lyrics2 = [[Kumaar]]\n| music2 = Meet Bros Anjjan\n| length2 = 05:00\n| title3 = Tu Hi Tu\n| extra3 = Mohammad Irfan\n| lyrics3 = Shabbir Ahmed\n| music3 = Himesh Reshammiya\n| length3 = 04:07\n| title4 = Go Go Go Govinda\n| extra4 = [[Mika Singh]], Shreya Ghoshal\n| lyrics4 = [[Swanand Kirkire]]\n| music4 = Himesh Reshammiya\n| length4 = 05:06\n| title5 = Hari Bol\n| extra5 = [[Keerthi Sagathia]]\n| lyrics5 = Subrat Sinha\n| music5 = Sachin - Jigar\n| length5 = 04:37\n| title6 = Tu Hi Tu (Reprise)\n| extra6 = Suraj Jagan\n| lyrics6 = Shabbir Ahmed\n| music6 = Himesh Reshammiya\n| length6 = 04:07\n| title7 = Oh My God (Title Track)\n| extra7 = Zubeen Garg\n| lyrics7 = Kumaar\n| music7 = Himesh Reshammiya\n| length7 = 01:28\n| title8 = Tu Hi Tu (Unplugged)\n| extra8 = Ash King\n| lyrics8 = Shabbir Ahmed\n| music8 = Himesh Reshammiya\n| length8 = 03:09\n| title9 = Go Go Govinda (Reprise)\n| extra9 = [[Aman Trikha]], Shreya Ghoshal\n| lyrics9 = Swanand Kirkire\n| music9 = Himesh Reshammiya\n| length9 = 05:08\n| title10 = Don't Worry (Remix)\n| extra10 = Himesh Reshammiya, Benny Dayal, Arya Acharya\n| lyrics10 = Shabbir Ahmed\n| music10 = Himesh Reshammiya\n| length10 = 03:31\n| title11 = Tu Hi Tu (Remix)\n| extra11 = Mohammad Irfan\n| lyrics11 = Shabbir Ahmed\n| music11 = Himesh Reshammiya\n| length11 = 04:17\n| title12 = Krishna Theme (Flute)\n| extra12 = Parash Nath and Sunit Kumar\n| lyrics12 = Kumaar\n| music12 = Meet Bros Anjjan\n| length12 = 02:07\n| all_writing = \n| total_length = \n}}\n\n==Release==\n''OMG \u2013 Oh My God!'' released worldwide on 28 September 2012.<ref name=cast/> Prior to its theatrical release, the [[Central Board of Film Certification]] (CBFC) certified the film with a [[U (Central Board of Film Certification)|U certificate]].\n\n==Critical reception==\n\nThe film was critically well received.<ref>{{cite web|title=Oh My God Reviews|url=http://www.indicine.com/bollywood/oh-my-god/reviews/|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131102161650/http://www.indicine.com/bollywood/oh-my-god/reviews/|archivedate=2 November 2013|url-status=dead|publisher=Indicine|df=dmy-all|access-date=1 October 2012}}</ref>\n\n[[Taran Adarsh]] of Bollywood Hungama gave the film 3.5 out of 5 stars and said \"On the whole, OMG \u2013 OH MY GOD! is a thought-provoking adaptation of a massively successful play. A movie tackling a sensitive and an untouched subject matter, it will find its share of advocates and adversaries, but the social message the movie conveys comes across loud and clear and that's one of the prime reasons why OMG becomes a deserving watch\".<ref>{{cite web|last=Adarsh|first=Taran|title=Taran Adarsh review|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/criticreview/id/549384|publisher=[[Bollywood Hungama]]|date=27 September 2012|accessdate=27 September 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131103104957/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/criticreview/id/549384|archivedate=3 November 2013|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Sukanya Verma of [[Rediff]] rated it 4 out of 5 reviewing \"A brave and absorbing blend of satire, fable and fantasy that brings our attention to the misuse and commercialisation of religion\".<ref>{{cite web|last=Verma|first=Sukanya|title=Review: OMG \u2013 Oh My God is brave and absorbing|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/review/review-oh-my-god-is-a-brave-absorbing-take-on-religion/20120928.htm|publisher=[[Rediff.com]]|date=28 September 2012|accessdate=28 September 2012|archivedate=30 September 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120930040448/http://www.rediff.com/movies/review/review-oh-my-god-is-a-brave-absorbing-take-on-religion/20120928.htm|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> [[Faisal Saif]] of Independent Bollywood rated it 4 out of 5 and said \"Strongly Recommended. Fearless concept with some Fearless performances\".<ref>{{cite news|last=Saif|first=Faisal|accessdate=29 September 2012|title=OMG: Oh My God|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/movie-review/OMG-Oh-My-God/movie-review/16545873.cms|newspaper=The Times of India|archivedate=1 November 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131101050223/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/movie-review/OMG-Oh-My-God/movie-review/16545873.cms|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n== Box office ==\n\nThe film had a low opening but showed good growth on its 2nd and 3rd day and collected {{INRConvert|30|m|nolink=yes}} nett in its opening weekend.<ref>{{cite web|title=OMG! Oh My God Picks Up Over Weekend|url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxnewsdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=4939&nCat=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121003231801/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxnewsdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=4939&nCat=|url-status=dead|archive-date=3 October 2012|date=1 October 2012|publisher=Box Office India|accessdate=1 October 2012|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Despite slow start, the film managed to gross collections of {{INRConvert|357.4|m|nolink=yes}} nett in its first week.<ref name=\"first week\">{{cite web|url=http://boxofficeindia.com/boxnewsdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=4960&nCat=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121011063543/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxnewsdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=4960&nCat=|url-status=dead|archive-date=11 October 2012|title=OMG! Oh My God Week One Territorial Breakdown|publisher=Box Office India|date=1 October 2011|accessdate=6 October 2012|df=dmy-all}}</ref> The film collected {{INRConvert|220|m|nolink=yes}} in its second week.<ref name=\"second week\">{{cite web |title=Aiyaa Bhoot Returns Dull Oh! My God Excellent Second Week |date=13 October 2011 |url=http://boxofficeindia.com/boxdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=4973&nCat= |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121016023757/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=4973&nCat= |url-status=dead |archive-date=16 October 2012 |publisher=Box Office India |df=dmy-all }}</ref> The film continued its successful run in its third week and make a total of around {{INRConvert|725.0|m|nolink=yes}} in three weeks.<ref name=\"three weeks\">{{cite web|title=Student Of The Year Opens Well Oh! My God Excellent Third Week|url=http://boxofficeindia.com/boxdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=4997&nCat=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121022184638/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=4997&nCat=|url-status=dead|archive-date=22 October 2012|publisher=Box Office India|date=20 October 2012|accessdate=20 October 2012|df=dmy-all}}</ref> The film raked another {{INRConvert|62.4|m|nolink=yes}} in its fourth week to make a total of {{INRConvert|782.4|m|nolink=yes}} in four weeks.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://upcomingmoviesdate.com/omg-oh-god-week-four-box-office-collection/|title=OMG! Oh My God Week Four Box Office Collection - Upcoming Movies Release Date|last=Yadav|first=Amit|date=2012-10-25|work=UMD|access-date=2017-05-28|language=en-US}}</ref> Overseas, ''OMG \u2013 Oh My God!'' grossed [[US$]]2.5 million in 10 days.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/overdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=4968&nCat=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121012235325/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/overdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=4968&nCat=|url-status=dead|archive-date=12 October 2012|title=English Vinglish Is Excellent Overseas|publisher=[[Box Office India]]|date=10 October 2012|accessdate=10 October 2012|df=dmy-all}}</ref> At the end of 17 days, ''OMG \u2013 Oh My God!'' had grossed {{INRConvert|104.5|m|nolink=yes}}.<ref>{{cite web|title=Aiyaa Bhoot Returns Dull English Vinglish Is HIT Overseas |url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/overdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=4989&nCat= |archive-url=https://archive.today/20121209032123/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/overdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=4989&nCat= |url-status=dead |archive-date=2012-12-09 |publisher=Box Office India }}</ref>\n\n==Controversy==\n{{cleanup|section|reason=These controversies are vague and do not tell readers what the actual complaints were, how Hindu gods were depicted, etc. There is also no other viewpoint challenging the complaints, which means we might be placing an undue emphasis on one viewpoint, which seems to contravene [[WP:NPOV|our policy on neutrality]].|date=November 2019}}\nThe film generated some controversy over the depictions of prominent [[Hinduism|Hindu]] gods and Indian spiritual traditions. [[Jalandhar]] State Mahila Congress Vice President Nimisha Mehta lodged a complaint against the lead actors, [[Paresh Rawal]] and [[Akshay Kumar]], and the producers of the film, for hurting religious sentiments of Hindus.<ref name=\"Controversy\">{{cite web|title=Oh My God: Police complaint against Akshay, Paresh Rawal|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-09-26/news-interviews/34100824_1_hindus-akshay-kumar-dialogues|newspaper=[[The Times of India]]|date=26 September 2012|accessdate=1 October 2012|archivedate=26 February 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130226151722/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-09-26/news-interviews/34100824_1_hindus-akshay-kumar-dialogues|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> The notice asked them to delete objectionable scenes and dialogues.<ref name=\"Controversy\"/> [[Akshay Kumar]] was given police protection, after this incident.<ref name=\"complaints\">{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-09-29/news-interviews/34163120_1_akshay-kumar-akki-security-guards|title='Oh My God' complaints|work=The Times of India|date=29 September 2012|accessdate=8 October 2012|author=Lalwani Vickey|location=Mumbai|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131103183426/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-09-29/news-interviews/34163120_1_akshay-kumar-akki-security-guards|archivedate=3 November 2013|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nThe film was banned in the [[United Arab Emirates]].<ref name=\"Banned\">{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-09-29/news-interviews/34149099_1_uae-hindi-film-vishesh-films|title=Oh My God axed in UAE|work=[[The Times of India]]|date=29 September 2012|accessdate=8 October 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131103183624/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-09-29/news-interviews/34149099_1_uae-hindi-film-vishesh-films|url-status=live|archivedate=3 November 2013|author=Lalwani, Vickey|location=Mumbai|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Vikram Malhotra of Viacom18 Pictures told the ''Hindustan Times'': \"We haven't been given an official statement yet, but from what we've been told, the content of the movie is too sensitive.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/bollywood/news/a408969/akshay-kumar-film-omg-oh-my-god-to-be-banned-in-uae.html#~p3alHdY5qkKZSM|title=Akshay Kumar's OMG to be banned in UAE?|date=28 September 2012|publisher=}}</ref>\n\nOn 12 July 2014, [[Madhya Pradesh High Court]] under the bench of Justice Ajay Manik Rao Khanwilkar and [[Alok Aradhe]] issued a notice to Akshay Kumar and Paresh Rawal for hurting religious sentiments of Hindus.<ref>{{cite news|title=Court issues notices to Akshay, Paresh Rawal|url=http://www.patrika.com/article/court-issues-notices-to-akshay-paresh-rawal/47638|accessdate=12 July 2014|work=Patrika Group|date=12 July 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714163155/http://www.patrika.com/article/court-issues-notices-to-akshay-paresh-rawal/47638|archivedate=14 July 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n==Awards==\nThe movie was awarded the Best Hindi film award by Institute for Research and Documentation in Social Sciences (IRDS) during the second IRDS Hindi Film Awards for social concern. The film has won the award for [[Academy Award for Best Adapted Screenplay|Best Adapted Screenplay]] in [[60th National Film Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|author=: 24 Jan 2013 04:10 pm|url=http://www.indiantelevision.com/aac/y2k13/aac44.php|title=OMG, Paan Singh Tomar receive awards for spreading social messages &#124; Indian Television Dot Com|publisher=Indiantelevision.com|date=24 January 2013|accessdate=5 August 2014|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131102222315/http://www.indiantelevision.com/aac/y2k13/aac44.php|archivedate=2 November 2013|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Religious satire]]\n*[[Bhagavad Gita trial in Russia]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb title|2283748|OMG \u2013 Oh My God!}}\n*{{Rotten Tomatoes|omg_oh_my_god}}\n\n{{Akshay Kumar}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:OMG - Oh My God!}}\n[[Category:2012 films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:2010s Hindi-language films]]\n[[Category:2010s comedy-drama films]]\n[[Category:Indian satirical films]]\n[[Category:Films set in Mumbai]]\n[[Category:Indian comedy-drama films]]\n[[Category:Fictional lawsuits against God]]\n[[Category:Indian courtroom films]]\n[[Category:Fictional lawsuits]]\n[[Category:2010s fantasy-comedy films]]\n[[Category:Hindi films remade in other languages]]\n[[Category:Indian fantasy-comedy films]]\n[[Category:Indian religious comedy films]]\n[[Category:Indian films based on plays]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Amar Mohile]]\n[[Category:Films whose writer won the Best Adapted Screenplay National Film Award]]\n[[Category:Viacom18 Motion Pictures films]]\n[[Category:Films featuring an item number]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2012 film directed by Umesh Shukla}}\n{{Other uses|Oh My God (disambiguation){{!}}Oh My God}}\n{{Distinguish|Oh, My God (2008 film)}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2013}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=May 2013}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = OMG \u2013 Oh My God!\n| image          = OMG Poster.png\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Umesh Shukla]]<ref name=\"cast\" />\n| producer       = [[Paresh Rawal]]<br>[[Akshay Kumar]]<br>[[Ashvini Yardi]]\n| writer         = Will Umesh Shukla\n| based on       = ''\"Kanji Virrudh Kanji\"''<ref>{{cite news|url=https://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/bollywood/akshay-waiting-for-twinkle-to-see-oh-my-god_120487.html|title=Akshay waiting for Twinkle to see 'Oh My God'|newspaper=[[The Times of India]]|accessdate=9 October 2012|date=6 October 2012}}</ref>\n| starring       = [[Paresh Rawal]]<br>[[Akshay Kumar]]<br>[[Mithun Chakraborty]]\n| music          = '''Score:'''<br>[[Amar Mohile]]<br>'''Songs:'''<br>[[Himesh Reshammiya]]<br>[[Sachin-Jigar]]<br>[[Meet Bros|Meet Bros. Anjjan]]\n| cinematography = [[Sethu Sriram]]\n| editing        = Tushar Shivan<br/>Rajesh Panchal\n| studio         = [[Grazing Goat Pictures Pvt. Ltd|Grazing Goat Pictures]]<br>[[Wave Group|Wave Cinemas]]<br>Spice Studios\n| distributor    = [[Viacom 18 Motion Pictures]]\n| released       = {{Film date|df=yes|2012|9|28}}\n| runtime        = 130 minutes<ref name=\"Runtime\">{{cite web|title=OMG - OH MY GOD! (PG) - British Board of Film Classification|url=http://www.bbfc.co.uk/releases/omg-oh-my-god-2012-0|publisher=[[British Board of Film Classification]]|accessdate=24 October 2012|date=19 September 2012}}</ref>\n| country        = India\n| language       = Hindi\n| budget         = {{INR}}200 million\n<ref>https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/oh-my-god-the-film-is-a-hit/story-CyGWSR6qRQowIi1b0DS8OL.html</ref>\n| gross          = {{INR}}1.22 billion\n<ref>{{cite web|url=http://boxofficeindia.com/Star_Cast/actor_record_world_total/akshay_kumar/actor |title=Archived copy |accessdate=5 September 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150804025031/http://boxofficeindia.com/Star_Cast/actor_record_world_total/akshay_kumar/actor |archivedate=4 August 2015 }}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''OMG \u2013 Oh My God!''''' is a 2012 Indian [[Hindi]]-language [[Satire|satirical]] comedy drama film which is an official remake of the 2001 Australian film ''[[The Man Who Sued God]]''. The storyline is based on a [[Gujarati language|Gujarati]] stage-play entitled ''Kanji Virudh Kanji.'' It is directed by [[Umesh Shukla]]. The film features [[Paresh Rawal]] and [[Akshay Kumar]] in the lead roles, along with [[Mithun Chakraborty]], [[Om Puri]], [[Govind Namdeo]], [[Nikhil Ratnaparkhi]], [[Poonam Jhawer]], [[Puja Gupta (actress)|Puja Gupta]] and [[Mahesh Manjrekar]] in the pivotal roles.<ref name=\"release\">{{cite web|title=The underlying message of Khiladi Kumar\u2019s forthcoming comedy|url=http://www.bollywoodlife.com/news-gossip/how-did-omg-oh-my-god-change-akshay-kumar/|publisher=Bollywood Life|date=17 September 2012|accessdate=7 October 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121006110935/http://www.bollywoodlife.com/news-gossip/how-did-omg-oh-my-god-change-akshay-kumar/|url-status=live|archivedate=6 October 2012|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Made on a budget of {{INRConvert|20|c|nolink=yes}}, the film released on 28 September 2012 to critical acclaim.<ref name=\"Budget\">{{cite web|title=Oh my God, the film is a hit!|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Bollywood/Oh-my-God-the-film-is-a-hit/Article1-938714.aspx|newspaper=[[Hindustan Times]]|accessdate=2 October 2012|date=2 October 2012|author=Shalvi Mangaokar|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131103232846/http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Bollywood/Oh-my-God-the-film-is-a-hit/Article1-938714.aspx|url-status=live|archivedate=3 November 2013|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"review\">{{cite web|title=OMG (OH MY GOD) movie review|url=http://www.reviewgang.com/movies/322-OMG-Oh-My-God-movie-review|publisher=Review Gang|accessdate=15 October 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121015090218/http://www.reviewgang.com/movies/322-OMG-Oh-My-God-movie-review|url-status=live|archivedate=15 October 2012|df=dmy-all}}</ref> The film was remade in Telugu as ''[[Gopala Gopala (2015 film)|Gopala Gopala]]'' in 2015 with [[Daggubati Venkatesh|Venkatesh]] and [[Pawan Kalyan]] in the lead roles and in Kannada with [[Upendra (actor)|Upendra]] and [[Sudeep]] titled as ''[[Mukunda Murari]] in 2016''.\n\n==Plot==\nKanji Lalji Mehta ([[Paresh Rawal]]), a middle-class [[atheism in Hinduism|atheist Hindu]] owns a shop of Hindu idols and antiques in [[Mumbai]]. He makes fun of religious activities around him and one such day, a low-intensity earthquake hits the city, and Kanji's shop is the only shop that is destroyed. His family and friends blame this on his atheism.\n\nAt the insurance office, Kanji learns that the disaster claim does not cover any damage caused by natural calamities classified under \"[[Act of God]]\". Running out of options, he decides to sue God but fails to find a lawyer for such a lawsuit. Hanif Qureshi ([[Om Puri]]), a poor Muslim lawyer, helps him file the case after Kanji decides to fight on his own. Legal notices are sent to the insurance company as well as to religious priests, Siddheshwar Maharaj, Gopi Maiyya, and their group's founder, Leeladhar Swamy ([[Mithun Chakraborty]]), summoning them to court as representatives of God.\n\nAs the court case commences and gains traction for its bizarre quality, Kanji finds himself facing armed fundamentalists and harassment, with his mortgage bank occupying the house, and his wife and kids leaving him. He is rescued from all of this by Krishna Vasudev Yadav ([[Akshay Kumar]]), who claims to be a real estate agent originally from [[Gokul]], [[Uttar Pradesh]], but appears to do fantastical tricks not possible for a human.\n\nThe lawsuit causes a public outcry. On Krishna's advice, Kanji goes to the media and gets wide coverage. Many people in a similar situation join him in the lawsuit, causing the amount of claims to skyrocket and [[Catholicism|Catholic]] priests and Muslim [[Mullah]]s to also be summoned as defendants. When the court demands written proof that the earthquake was an 'Act of God,' Krishna steers Kanji toward holy books like [[Bhagavad Gita]], [[The Quran]] and [[The Bible]]. Kanji reads them and finds a passage in each that says the world and all that happen in it, from beginning to end, is a creation of God and comes from God's will alone. This strengthens his case and increases public support. However, Kanji suffers a stroke in court and is rushed to the hospital where he goes into a coma and is paralyzed. When he opens his eyes after a month, he finds Krishna, who reveals that he is God, and proves it by curing Kanji completely. He further reveals that He created the entire world, animals and humans but not any religion, and he was the one who destroyed Kanji's shop because he wanted to punish the godmen who showed his fear to public, to earn money when in fact, He wants his creations to love him. He figured out that Kanji would end up exposing them if he destroys his Shop. \n\nKanji learns that the lawsuit's verdict was in his favor and religious organizations were ordered by court to pay the compensation to all the plaintiffs; people have begun revering Kanji himself as a god. Leeladhar, Gopi Maiyya, and Siddheshwar have taken advantage of this by opening a temple dedicated to Kanji and accumulating millions in donations. Krishna explains to Kanji that his job as God is to show people right and wrong - people do with it what they will. Kanji decides to fight back. He breaks his own statue, admonishing the crowd about trusting in God-men. He advises them to search for God in themselves and in others, not in statues; that God is everywhere, not just in temples, and faith should come from within. He tells them not to believe in fraudulent God-men, as their job is to turn religion into business.\n\nKrishna looks on proudly as Kanji speaks, then vanishes when Kanji tries to reach him after. Kanji is reunited with his family and sees Krishna's key chain on the ground. When he is about to keep it, he hears Krishna's voice, telling him to get rid of the key chain as fear of God and reliance on religious objects was what he'd fought against all this time. Kanji smiles and throws it away, watching as it disappears in the sky with a flash.<ref name=cast>{{cite web|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/cast/id/549384|title=OMG Oh My God! Cast & Crew|publisher=Bollywood Hungama|accessdate=10 October 2012|author=Taran Adarsh|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121010052818/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/cast/id/549384|archivedate=10 October 2012|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n{{div col begin}}\n*[[Paresh Rawal]] as Kanji Lalji Mehta\n*[[Akshay Kumar]] as Krishna Vasudev Yadav / [[Lord Krishna]]\n*[[Mithun Chakraborty]] as Leeladhar Swamy\n*[[Govind Namdeo]] as Siddheshwar Maharaj\n*[[Poonam Jhawer]] as Gopi Maiyya\n*[[Om Puri]] as Advocate Hanif Qureshi\n*[[Mahesh Manjrekar]] as Advocate Sardesai\n*[[Puja Gupta (actress)|Puja Gupta]] as Hanif's Daughter\n*Yousuf Hussain Khan as Judge\n*[[Lubna Salim]] as Susheela (Kanji's wife)\n*[[Nidhi Subbaiah]] as Shweta Tiwari (News reporter)\n*[[Murli Sharma]] as Laxman Mishra\n*[[Tisca Chopra]] as The interview host\n*Bhanu Prasad as The Pujari\n*[[Ishita Vyas]] Manju Vyas as The Sardesai's assistant\n*Nikhil Ratnaparkhi as Mahadev\n*[[Arun Bali]] as Accha Sadhu\n*Jaineeraj Rajpurohit as Dinesh Gandhi\n*[[Apoorva Arora]] as Jigna (Kanji's daughter)\n*Azaan Rustam Shah as Chintu (Kanji's son)\n*[[Honey Chhaya]] as Jagdishbhai\n*Manu Narula as Krishna\n*Gopal Pathak\n*[[Prabhu Deva]] in a special appearance in the song \"Go Go Go Govinda\"\n*[[Sonakshi Sinha]] in a special appearance in the song \"Go Go Go Govinda\"\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Production==\nProducer [[Akshay Kumar]] announced the film in 2012. [[Paresh Rawal]] who appeared in the original play ''Kishen vs Kanhaiya'' was cast in the lead role with Akshay Kumar playing the role of Krishna in the movie.<ref name=\"cast\"/> [[Mithun Chakraborty]] played a supporting role in the film. The filming was reported to have begun in January 2012.<ref name=appearance>{{cite news|title=Special appearance in 'OMG'|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-07-29/news-interviews/32923154_1_prabhu|accessdate=7 October 2012|newspaper=[[The Times of India]]|date=29 Jul 2012}} {{Dead link|date=October 2014}}</ref> Director [[Prabhu Deva]] appeared in an item-number along with [[Sonakshi Sinha]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/salman-khan-vs-srk-in-akshay-kumars-oh-my-god/236322-8-66.html|publisher=[[IBN Live]]|title=Akshay and Paresh together again?|date=2 January 2012|accessdate=21 March 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120307204836/http://ibnlive.in.com/news/salman-khan-vs-srk-in-akshay-kumars-oh-my-god/236322-8-66.html|archivedate=7 March 2012|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n==Soundtrack==\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = OMG \u2013 Oh My God!\n| type         = Soundtrack\n| artist       = [[Himesh Reshammiya]], [[Sachin - Jigar]] and [[Meet Bros Anjjan]]\n| cover        = \n| alt          = \n| released     = 12 September 2012\n| recorded     = \n| venue        = \n| studio       = \n| genre        = [[Film soundtrack|Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length       = \n| label        = [[T-Series (company)|T-Series]]\n| producer     = [[Himesh Reshammiya]]<br>[[Sachin - Jigar]]<br>[[Meet Bros Anjjan]]\n| prev_title   = \n| prev_year    = \n| next_title   = \n| next_year    = \n}}\n\nThe soundtrack of ''OMG \u2013 Oh My God!'' is composed by [[Himesh Reshammiya]], [[Sachin - Jigar]] and [[Meet Bros Anjjan]], whilst the lyrics have been penned by [[Shabbir Ahmed (lyricist)|Shabbir Ahmed]], [[Kumaar]], [[Swanand Kirkire]] and Subrat Sinha. The album features vocals by Reshammiya, [[Shreya Ghoshal]], [[Kailash Kher]], [[Benny Dayal]], [[Ash King]], [[Suraj Jagan]], [[Keerthi Sagathia]], [[Zubeen Garg]], [[Meet Bros Anjjan]], Arya Acharya, Mohd Irfan, [[Aman Trikha]] and Parash Nath. The full audio album was launched on 12 September 2012 by [[T-Series (company)|T-Series]].\n\n{{Track listing\n| extra_column = Singer(s)\n| all_lyrics = \n| title1 = Don't Worry (Hey Ram)\n| extra1 = Himesh Reshammiya, Benny Dayal, Arya Acharya\n| lyrics1 = [[Shabbir Ahmed (lyricist)|Shabbir Ahmed]]\n| music1 = Himesh Reshammiya\n| length1 = 05:04\n| title2 = Mere Nishaan\n| extra2 = [[Kailash Kher]], Meet Bros Anjjan\n| lyrics2 = [[Kumaar]]\n| music2 = Meet Bros Anjjan\n| length2 = 05:00\n| title3 = Tu Hi Tu\n| extra3 = Mohammad Irfan\n| lyrics3 = Shabbir Ahmed\n| music3 = Himesh Reshammiya\n| length3 = 04:07\n| title4 = Go Go Go Govinda\n| extra4 = [[Mika Singh]], Shreya Ghoshal\n| lyrics4 = [[Swanand Kirkire]]\n| music4 = Himesh Reshammiya\n| length4 = 05:06\n| title5 = Hari Bol\n| extra5 = [[Keerthi Sagathia]]\n| lyrics5 = Subrat Sinha\n| music5 = Sachin - Jigar\n| length5 = 04:37\n| title6 = Tu Hi Tu (Reprise)\n| extra6 = Suraj Jagan\n| lyrics6 = Shabbir Ahmed\n| music6 = Himesh Reshammiya\n| length6 = 04:07\n| title7 = Oh My God (Title Track)\n| extra7 = Zubeen Garg\n| lyrics7 = Kumaar\n| music7 = Himesh Reshammiya\n| length7 = 01:28\n| title8 = Tu Hi Tu (Unplugged)\n| extra8 = Ash King\n| lyrics8 = Shabbir Ahmed\n| music8 = Himesh Reshammiya\n| length8 = 03:09\n| title9 = Go Go Govinda (Reprise)\n| extra9 = [[Aman Trikha]], Shreya Ghoshal\n| lyrics9 = Swanand Kirkire\n| music9 = Himesh Reshammiya\n| length9 = 05:08\n| title10 = Don't Worry (Remix)\n| extra10 = Himesh Reshammiya, Benny Dayal, Arya Acharya\n| lyrics10 = Shabbir Ahmed\n| music10 = Himesh Reshammiya\n| length10 = 03:31\n| title11 = Tu Hi Tu (Remix)\n| extra11 = Mohammad Irfan\n| lyrics11 = Shabbir Ahmed\n| music11 = Himesh Reshammiya\n| length11 = 04:17\n| title12 = Krishna Theme (Flute)\n| extra12 = Parash Nath and Sunit Kumar\n| lyrics12 = Kumaar\n| music12 = Meet Bros Anjjan\n| length12 = 02:07\n| all_writing = \n| total_length = \n}}\n\n==Release==\n''OMG \u2013 Oh My God!'' released worldwide on 28 September 2012.<ref name=cast/> Prior to its theatrical release, the [[Central Board of Film Certification]] (CBFC) certified the film with a [[U (Central Board of Film Certification)|U certificate]].\n\n==Critical reception==\n\nThe film was critically well received.<ref>{{cite web|title=Oh My God Reviews|url=http://www.indicine.com/bollywood/oh-my-god/reviews/|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131102161650/http://www.indicine.com/bollywood/oh-my-god/reviews/|archivedate=2 November 2013|url-status=dead|publisher=Indicine|df=dmy-all|access-date=1 October 2012}}</ref>\n\n[[Taran Adarsh]] of Bollywood Hungama gave the film 3.5 out of 5 stars and said \"On the whole, OMG \u2013 OH MY GOD! is a thought-provoking adaptation of a massively successful play. A movie tackling a sensitive and an untouched subject matter, it will find its share of advocates and adversaries, but the social message the movie conveys comes across loud and clear and that's one of the prime reasons why OMG becomes a deserving watch\".<ref>{{cite web|last=Adarsh|first=Taran|title=Taran Adarsh review|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/criticreview/id/549384|publisher=[[Bollywood Hungama]]|date=27 September 2012|accessdate=27 September 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131103104957/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/criticreview/id/549384|archivedate=3 November 2013|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Sukanya Verma of [[Rediff]] rated it 4 out of 5 reviewing \"A brave and absorbing blend of satire, fable and fantasy that brings our attention to the misuse and commercialisation of religion\".<ref>{{cite web|last=Verma|first=Sukanya|title=Review: OMG \u2013 Oh My God is brave and absorbing|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/review/review-oh-my-god-is-a-brave-absorbing-take-on-religion/20120928.htm|publisher=[[Rediff.com]]|date=28 September 2012|accessdate=28 September 2012|archivedate=30 September 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120930040448/http://www.rediff.com/movies/review/review-oh-my-god-is-a-brave-absorbing-take-on-religion/20120928.htm|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> [[Faisal Saif]] of Independent Bollywood rated it 4 out of 5 and said \"Strongly Recommended. Fearless concept with some Fearless performances\".<ref>{{cite news|last=Saif|first=Faisal|accessdate=29 September 2012|title=OMG: Oh My God|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/movie-review/OMG-Oh-My-God/movie-review/16545873.cms|newspaper=The Times of India|archivedate=1 November 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131101050223/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/movie-review/OMG-Oh-My-God/movie-review/16545873.cms|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n== Box office ==\n\nThe film had a low opening but showed good growth on its 2nd and 3rd day and collected {{INRConvert|30|m|nolink=yes}} nett in its opening weekend.<ref>{{cite web|title=OMG! Oh My God Picks Up Over Weekend|url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxnewsdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=4939&nCat=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121003231801/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxnewsdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=4939&nCat=|url-status=dead|archive-date=3 October 2012|date=1 October 2012|publisher=Box Office India|accessdate=1 October 2012|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Despite slow start, the film managed to gross collections of {{INRConvert|357.4|m|nolink=yes}} nett in its first week.<ref name=\"first week\">{{cite web|url=http://boxofficeindia.com/boxnewsdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=4960&nCat=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121011063543/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxnewsdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=4960&nCat=|url-status=dead|archive-date=11 October 2012|title=OMG! Oh My God Week One Territorial Breakdown|publisher=Box Office India|date=1 October 2011|accessdate=6 October 2012|df=dmy-all}}</ref> The film collected {{INRConvert|220|m|nolink=yes}} in its second week.<ref name=\"second week\">{{cite web |title=Aiyaa Bhoot Returns Dull Oh! My God Excellent Second Week |date=13 October 2011 |url=http://boxofficeindia.com/boxdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=4973&nCat= |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121016023757/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=4973&nCat= |url-status=dead |archive-date=16 October 2012 |publisher=Box Office India |df=dmy-all }}</ref> The film continued its successful run in its third week and make a total of around {{INRConvert|725.0|m|nolink=yes}} in three weeks.<ref name=\"three weeks\">{{cite web|title=Student Of The Year Opens Well Oh! My God Excellent Third Week|url=http://boxofficeindia.com/boxdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=4997&nCat=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121022184638/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=4997&nCat=|url-status=dead|archive-date=22 October 2012|publisher=Box Office India|date=20 October 2012|accessdate=20 October 2012|df=dmy-all}}</ref> The film raked another {{INRConvert|62.4|m|nolink=yes}} in its fourth week to make a total of {{INRConvert|782.4|m|nolink=yes}} in four weeks.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://upcomingmoviesdate.com/omg-oh-god-week-four-box-office-collection/|title=OMG! Oh My God Week Four Box Office Collection - Upcoming Movies Release Date|last=Yadav|first=Amit|date=2012-10-25|work=UMD|access-date=2017-05-28|language=en-US}}</ref> Overseas, ''OMG \u2013 Oh My God!'' grossed [[US$]]2.5 million in 10 days.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/overdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=4968&nCat=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121012235325/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/overdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=4968&nCat=|url-status=dead|archive-date=12 October 2012|title=English Vinglish Is Excellent Overseas|publisher=[[Box Office India]]|date=10 October 2012|accessdate=10 October 2012|df=dmy-all}}</ref> At the end of 17 days, ''OMG \u2013 Oh My God!'' had grossed {{INRConvert|104.5|m|nolink=yes}}.<ref>{{cite web|title=Aiyaa Bhoot Returns Dull English Vinglish Is HIT Overseas |url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/overdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=4989&nCat= |archive-url=https://archive.today/20121209032123/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/overdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=4989&nCat= |url-status=dead |archive-date=2012-12-09 |publisher=Box Office India }}</ref>\n\n==Controversy==\n{{cleanup|section|reason=These controversies are vague and do not tell readers what the actual complaints were, how Hindu gods were depicted, etc. There is also no other viewpoint challenging the complaints, which means we might be placing an undue emphasis on one viewpoint, which seems to contravene [[WP:NPOV|our policy on neutrality]].|date=November 2019}}\nThe film generated some controversy over the depictions of prominent [[Hinduism|Hindu]] gods and Indian spiritual traditions. [[Jalandhar]] State Mahila Congress Vice President Nimisha Mehta lodged a complaint against the lead actors, [[Paresh Rawal]] and [[Akshay Kumar]], and the producers of the film, for hurting religious sentiments of Hindus.<ref name=\"Controversy\">{{cite web|title=Oh My God: Police complaint against Akshay, Paresh Rawal|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-09-26/news-interviews/34100824_1_hindus-akshay-kumar-dialogues|newspaper=[[The Times of India]]|date=26 September 2012|accessdate=1 October 2012|archivedate=26 February 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130226151722/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-09-26/news-interviews/34100824_1_hindus-akshay-kumar-dialogues|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> The notice asked them to delete objectionable scenes and dialogues.<ref name=\"Controversy\"/> [[Akshay Kumar]] was given police protection, after this incident.<ref name=\"complaints\">{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-09-29/news-interviews/34163120_1_akshay-kumar-akki-security-guards|title='Oh My God' complaints|work=The Times of India|date=29 September 2012|accessdate=8 October 2012|author=Lalwani Vickey|location=Mumbai|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131103183426/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-09-29/news-interviews/34163120_1_akshay-kumar-akki-security-guards|archivedate=3 November 2013|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nThe film was banned in the [[United Arab Emirates]].<ref name=\"Banned\">{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-09-29/news-interviews/34149099_1_uae-hindi-film-vishesh-films|title=Oh My God axed in UAE|work=[[The Times of India]]|date=29 September 2012|accessdate=8 October 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131103183624/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-09-29/news-interviews/34149099_1_uae-hindi-film-vishesh-films|url-status=live|archivedate=3 November 2013|author=Lalwani, Vickey|location=Mumbai|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Vikram Malhotra of Viacom18 Pictures told the ''Hindustan Times'': \"We haven't been given an official statement yet, but from what we've been told, the content of the movie is too sensitive.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/bollywood/news/a408969/akshay-kumar-film-omg-oh-my-god-to-be-banned-in-uae.html#~p3alHdY5qkKZSM|title=Akshay Kumar's OMG to be banned in UAE?|date=28 September 2012|publisher=}}</ref>\n\nOn 12 July 2014, [[Madhya Pradesh High Court]] under the bench of Justice Ajay Manik Rao Khanwilkar and [[Alok Aradhe]] issued a notice to Akshay Kumar and Paresh Rawal for hurting religious sentiments of Hindus.<ref>{{cite news|title=Court issues notices to Akshay, Paresh Rawal|url=http://www.patrika.com/article/court-issues-notices-to-akshay-paresh-rawal/47638|accessdate=12 July 2014|work=Patrika Group|date=12 July 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714163155/http://www.patrika.com/article/court-issues-notices-to-akshay-paresh-rawal/47638|archivedate=14 July 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n==Awards==\nThe movie was awarded the Best Hindi film award by Institute for Research and Documentation in Social Sciences (IRDS) during the second IRDS Hindi Film Awards for social concern. The film has won the award for [[Academy Award for Best Adapted Screenplay|Best Adapted Screenplay]] in [[60th National Film Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|author=: 24 Jan 2013 04:10 pm|url=http://www.indiantelevision.com/aac/y2k13/aac44.php|title=OMG, Paan Singh Tomar receive awards for spreading social messages &#124; Indian Television Dot Com|publisher=Indiantelevision.com|date=24 January 2013|accessdate=5 August 2014|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131102222315/http://www.indiantelevision.com/aac/y2k13/aac44.php|archivedate=2 November 2013|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Religious satire]]\n*[[Bhagavad Gita trial in Russia]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb title|2283748|OMG \u2013 Oh My God!}}\n*{{Rotten Tomatoes|omg_oh_my_god}}\n\n{{Akshay Kumar}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:OMG - Oh My God!}}\n[[Category:2012 films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:2010s Hindi-language films]]\n[[Category:2010s comedy-drama films]]\n[[Category:Indian satirical films]]\n[[Category:Films set in Mumbai]]\n[[Category:Indian comedy-drama films]]\n[[Category:Fictional lawsuits against God]]\n[[Category:Indian courtroom films]]\n[[Category:Fictional lawsuits]]\n[[Category:2010s fantasy-comedy films]]\n[[Category:Hindi films remade in other languages