\n", "text_old": "<!-- Please do not remove or change this AfD message until the discussion has been closed. -->\n{{Article for deletion/dated|page=American Sheriff|timestamp=20200401011219|year=2020|month=April|day=1|substed=yes|help=off}}\n<!-- Once discussion is closed, please place on talk page: {{Old AfD multi|page=American Sheriff|date=1 April 2020|result='''keep'''}} -->\n<!-- End of AfD message, feel free to edit beyond this point -->\n{{Unreferenced|date=March 2012}}\n{{Notability|Music|date=March 2012}}\n{{for|the law enforcement role in the United States|Sheriffs in the United States}}\n{{Infobox musical artist <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject Musicians -->\n| name                = '''American Sheriff'''\n| image               = \n| caption             = \n| image_size          = <!-- Only for images narrower than 220 pixels. Set the value as a number without \"px\". -->\n| background          = group_or_band\n| alias               = \n| origin              = \n| instrument          = \n| genre               = \n| occupation          = \n| years_active        = 2007 &ndash; present \n| label               = [[Imputor?]]\n| associated_acts     = [[Pleaseeasaur]], [[Plastiq Phantom]]\n| website             = \n| current_members     = [[JP Hasson]], [[Darrin Wiener]]\n| past_members        = \n}}\n\n'''American Sheriff''' is a musical collaboration between [[Pleaseeasaur]] and [[Plastiq Phantom]]. They describe their sound as \"going to Texas and getting ho-down happy\" which is reflected in the \"cowboy and Indian\" themes that they often use. Their first album, ''Long Arm of the Law'', was released in 2007 by [[Imputor?]].\n\n==Discography==\n* ''Long Arm of the Law'' (2007)\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.imputor.com/artists/18/American_Sheriff/ American Sheriff] at Imputor? Records\n* [http://www.last.fm/music/American+Sheriff American Sheriff] at Last.fm\n\n[[Category:American comedy musical groups]]\n", "name_user": "Scorpya401", "label": "unsafe", 